&lt;p&gt;I am much too lazy to actually leave your site to send you an email, or even type into the optional name box.  Since the &quot;actually pretty easy&quot; link you left sports a preposterous statistic that I am quite confident you made up, I figured I would turn to a more definitive source for answers.  When I typed &quot;what percentage of people on the internet are dudes&quot; into my Google chrome bar, the first link I came up with was:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;http://womansavers.com/infidelity-statistics.asp&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The third link was:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;http://www.focus.com/fyi/state-internet/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I lost interest after that.  Thanks, Google!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Depends what your definition of &quot;wasting your time&quot; is... really any game is a waste of time because its just entertainment that gives you no skills for the real world. So whether people wander around an open map, or kill monsters non-stop they are wasting time in both cases. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It depends on what a player enjoys. Some people (me for ex) do enjoy walking around from place to place with only occasional action. When theres non-stop action, i get bored easily because its the same thing over and over again. When action is sporadic, its new and refreshing each time. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I would conclude that the Skyrim model is the best, where it gives you an option to fast travel but ONLY to familiar places. Im playing Morrowind now though, and i dont mind the traveling.&lt;/p&gt;

