data.text:
&lt;p&gt;I came across a really cool web site.  It&#039;s called the &quot;rasturbator.&quot;  Before you start coming up with gross things that &quot;rasturbater&quot; could mean, I will tell you.  The site allows you to upload any picture of your choice, and it will blow it up, rasterize it (turn it into hundreds of little dots), and format it for print on a bunch of letter sized paper.  We found a nice picture of Keira Knightley, and &quot;rasturbated&quot; it (we had a lot of fun telling random people that we were rasturbating).  I have some great pictures, if you will just&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;click here . . .&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Ok, so there&#039;s this web site.  It&#039;s called &lt;a href =&quot; http://homokaasu.org/rasterbator/&quot;&gt;the Rasturbator&lt;/a&gt;, and it is totally cool.  Any web site that lets my friends and I yell sexual innuendo that isn&#039;t really innuendo is an awesome web site.  We needed something to liven up the hallway, because we were getting sick of the drab white walls, also the smell was getting pretty bad.  &quot;Lets get some hot chicks and put them up on the walls,&quot; we said.  What we meant, of course, was &quot;Some artful posters would be a nice contrast to the shades of grey present in this environment.&quot;  We&#039;re always so concious of good design.  &quot;Yeah, let&#039;s rasterbate (giggle) all over the wall (giggle).&quot;  &lt;i&gt;Come on, we&#039;re 18 year old college guys, what do you expect us to say?&lt;/i&gt;  We wanted to eventually have rasturbations (giggle) all up and down the hall, covering the entire hallway.  How totally awesome would that be?  Seriously.  So we did a google image search for a good picture of Keira Knightley, who we all adore so much.  Here&#039;s the image we selected:&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/keira.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/keirathumb.jpg&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; hspace=&quot;5&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Now, if this picture is offensive to anyone, please let me know.  I didn&#039;t think it would be a problem, which is why I selected Keira for this thing in the first place.  I didn&#039;t think anyone would be offended by pure un-flawed beauty, but, you know, it takes all kinds.  I though anyone who had a problem with this picture had problems of their own, because beauty this pure should not cause that response.  Anyway, we uploaded the image to the site, and made the measurements to come up with the size of the full image.  The final rasturbation (giggle) ended up using 72 sheets of standard letter sized paper.  We went on down to the computer lab (yes, you read that right) to print off the 72 sheets of pointillistic beauty.  We got the whole thing to print, giggling at the lab assistant the whole time.  Eventually our RA (we have a new RA named Zawar) came in and asked us what the hell we were doing, but we just giggled at him.  We were a little freaked out when we realized that each sheet of paper was not printed to the edge (of course), so we would need to hand-cut every single sheet to get them all to the right size.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;At this point, we had a pretty big group of people watching us, because it was a pretty cool thing, after all.  We gathered up the bundle, and started taping it to the wall, right outside my room.  Among the group of bystanders was a bunch of people from our hall, a few random girls, and Zawar himself (clear proof to us that we wouldn&#039;t get in trouble for it).  The final measurement came out to 7&#039;7&quot; tall by about 4&#039;6&quot; wide.  That&#039;s really big, by the way.  Everyone who saw it thought it was awesome.  People would walk though the hall, and right when they finished saying &quot;this hall smells like crap&quot; they would see the poster, and then they would say &quot;wow, this hall is awesome.&quot;  Mission: accomplished?  Unfortunately, not quite.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;IMAGE BONANZA!!!!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/raster001.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/raster1thumb.jpg&quot; title=&quot;The assembly.  Those are Zawar&#039;s legs propped on that chair.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/raster002.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/raster2thumb.jpg&quot; title=&quot;The finished rasturbation.  SO GORGEOUS!!&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/raster003.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/raster3thumb.jpg&quot; title=&quot;Fred was really proud of a job well done.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Ok, so now the bad news.  Zawar told us that as long as Jason (the head RA) is okay with it, it will stay.  We all figured that it would be okay, because we made it through an entire day with no removal-order.  Then at about 5 oclock, we get the bad news.  Zawar told us that we need to remove it, but that we could talk to Jason about it.  So we decided to talk to Jason about it.  It was a lot of work and awesomeness to just tear down.  Jason was an absolute asshole, though.  He just flat out told us, &quot;it&#039;s coming down, no question, you&#039;re taking it down.&quot;  We guessed that he was in a hurry, and we decided to talk to him on Monday (it was Friday at the time).  Later we get the order that it has to come down by Friday night.  Mission: Failed.  damn.  First the men&#039;s sign, then the giant poster.  What was his reasoning?  It was a fire hazard, and could be offensive to someone.  Right.  As if.  I ended up having to take it down, and I put it on my ceiling, over my bed (the only place large enough for it).  So now I look like some kind of weirdo with this huge picture right over my bed, but whatever.  It was fun, and it gave us something to do for a while.  Immediately after I took it down, someone was walking through the hall, and wondered where it went.  He doesn&#039;t even live here, but he was still mad that it came down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cafeteria in &lt;b&gt;Earhart&lt;/b&gt; hall serves a desert that they call &lt;b&gt;&quot;make your own dream.&quot;&lt;/b&gt;  They have these lousy cheescake things, with an assortment of toppings.  I looked at those toppings today, and I looked at that little sign they have.  &quot;Make your own dream&quot; is what &lt;b&gt;it&lt;/b&gt; says.  It belongs in one of those &lt;b&gt;futile motivational books&lt;/b&gt;.  The ones which only work because whoever is reading them decides to stop being an &lt;b&gt;asshole&lt;/b&gt; and just live like a human is supposed to.  &quot;Make your own dream&quot; sounds like some tagline from a bad &lt;b title=&quot;I know it&#039;s misspelled.  Why?&quot;&gt;Britni Spears&lt;/b&gt; song.  One of those purely commercial songs who&#039;s only purpose is to promote some &lt;b&gt;new product&lt;/b&gt;.  In the video, &lt;b title=&quot;Why indeed?&quot;&gt;Britni&lt;/b&gt; would wear some skimpy outfit and be one of those &lt;b&gt;assholes&lt;/b&gt; who needs a motivational book.  &quot;Make your own dream&quot; sounds like a slogan from an overused &lt;b&gt;armed forces&lt;/b&gt; commercial.  &quot;Make your own dream in the US Naval Marine Guard.  Fight for fredom clearing beaches of &lt;b&gt;empty beer cans&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;used condoms&lt;/b&gt;.&quot;   Why is it that people try to be motivational with stupid taglines like that, when the only useful application for it is a &lt;b&gt;mediocre dessert&lt;/b&gt;.  Of all the times anyone has ever said &quot;Make your own dream,&quot; it has only made sense when it was delivered with &lt;b&gt;canned strawberry-topping&lt;/b&gt; and crunched up &lt;b&gt;heath bars&lt;/b&gt;.  I made my own dream today with the toppings I chose, although I mostly just wanted &lt;b&gt;plain cheesecake&lt;/b&gt;.  I wish life were that easy.  I wish that every time something crappy happens to someone, they can just sprinkle M&amp;M&#039;s or canned strawberry-topping on it and make it their dream.  Maybe the world would be a little stickier, but would that be so bad?  How I wish life were that easy.  I am in desperate need of a dream, like that one where &lt;b&gt;Natalie Portman&lt;/b&gt; was in my kitchen at home.  I would love for that to happen, just for the pure value of being able to meet Natalie Portman.  Dreams come and go.  They sneak up on me and confuse me.  They excite me and they get my hopes up.  They never come true.  My dreams &lt;b&gt;never come true&lt;/b&gt;.  I can make all the dreams I want, but they will always just be dreams.  Everytime I think a dream has finally happened for me, it ends up being lousy cheesecake covered with canned strawberry-topping.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Don&#039;t sue me, Britni&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The wind can blow.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I am a blade of grass, wind cannot hurt me, I will only bend with it.  The rain only strengthens my roots.  The gardener cannot kill me, and in fact he helps me grow.  Nothing can hurt me, nothing can stop me.  I am eternal, because I will not be destroyed.  My mind is free.  My sense is clear.  Nothing hates me.  I accomodate all things: feet, livestock, trees, everything.  Anything that can happen to me will only strengthen me.  &lt;b&gt;I am now alive.&lt;/b&gt;  Goodbye Shauvon.  I am now &lt;i title=&quot;the true Gaelic spelling of my name&quot;&gt;Siobhan&lt;/i&gt;, a living member of this earth.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Although I may just keep signing my name &quot;Shauvon,&quot; just to keep things simpler.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I graduated from high school, I vowed that I would never return to that &lt;b&gt;awful place&lt;/b&gt;.  Don&#039;t get me wrong, Mt Vernon High School isn&#039;t the &lt;b title=&quot;I hear that Northern Siberia is a little cold this time of year.&quot;&gt;worst place in the world&lt;/b&gt;, it&#039;s just that high school wasn&#039;t my paticular cup of tea. I was so quick to forget high school, that I didn&#039;t even attend my own commencement, a fact that I &lt;b&gt;doubt&lt;/b&gt; I will ever regret. The last thing I want is something that will make me start to worry about the trappings and chore of a high school student once again.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Imagine my suprise, then, when I found myself doing exactly that.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;There&#039;s a hubbub going on in my hometown. It&#039;s a hubbub that threatens to consume the enire population in an epic stuggle, the likes of which haven&#039;t been seen since -- well, since the Bush administration came into office.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;What could it be?  Click here if you dare.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;All of the schools in the east-central Indiana area are balooning up more than a Thanksgiving day Parade.  These gigantic high schools are cropping up everywhere.  It&#039;s insane, the amount of students that are moving to the area.  Not to be outdone, Mt. Vernon school corporation has done some expansion of its own in the last couple years. To kick things off, Mt Vernon was proud to announce their new, &lt;b&gt;multi-milion dollar football statium&lt;/b&gt; two years ago. They also just built a huge &quot;intermediate school&quot; for just the 5th and 6th graders, further increasing the &lt;b&gt;age seggregation&lt;/b&gt; of modern public schools. Currently under construction, the McCordsville elementary will add to the sepparation of students along town borders. Indeed, it would seem that the Superintendant, &lt;b&gt;Dr. William Riggs&lt;/b&gt; will not stop until he has divided every student into a sepparate school, and sucked every last penny of tax money from the parents.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Oh, how I wish I was kidding.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;It would seem that &lt;b title=&quot;Direct Quote from the MVCSC website&quot;&gt;&quot;raising academic achievement for all students&quot;&lt;/b&gt; includes the construction of multi-million dollar buildings. The administration announced late last year their plans for their capricious new additions for the &quot;old &#039;n busted&quot; high school and existing elementaries. Included in this plan is a &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;$60 million addition&lt;/b&gt; to the high school, a &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;$27 million dollar addition&lt;/b&gt; to the two elementary schools, &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;$16 million for a new gym, pool, and auditorium&lt;/b&gt; for the high school,  a &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;technology center&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;i&gt;and&lt;/i&gt; a &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;new bus garage&lt;/b&gt;. First off, the school system has an auditorium, a pool, a bus garage, and a whopping &lt;i&gt;7 gyms&lt;/i&gt; at its disposal already. I&#039;m sorry if all of this seems a little redundant to me. The grand total for the whole project, according to the administration (and keep in mind that prices are very often not met, projects usually go over budget), is &lt;b&gt;136 million dollars&lt;/b&gt;.  That does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; include the two schools recently built, or the football stadium. Just to keep things in perspective, Conseco Fieldhouse, which is a multi-purpose arena for a professional basketball team, cost 174 million dollars (a difference of. . . 38 million dollars). Mt. Vernon school corp. services about &lt;b title=&quot;From the September 9th Schoolboard Minutes&quot;&gt;3,191&lt;/b&gt; students, which is one of the smallest corporations in the area, whereas the Fieldhouse can seat &lt;b title=&quot;Straight from the official Fieldhouse site&quot;&gt;18,345&lt;/b&gt;. Maybe those two things don&#039;t really compare, but it&#039;s worth noting.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Big deal&lt;/i&gt;, you say. &lt;i&gt;So what&lt;/i&gt;, you might scoff. A school is entitled to spend some money on &quot;raising academic achievement for all students&quot; if it wants to. If you find yourself saying those things, you might just want to listen to this. The proposed addition, all told, will increase property taxes of everyone in the area an estimated &lt;b title=&quot;From mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;60 - 85 percent&lt;/b&gt; from current levels over the next six years. What are your property taxes, I ask. Say you owe about $1,100 every year (that&#039;s when you don&#039;t count that storage shed as another structure). If you happened to be living in the Vernon township area over the next six years, and this whole deal goes through, you could be owing another $935. That&#039;s almost a &lt;b&gt;thousand dollars more&lt;/b&gt; that you will have to pay each year just for living in the Vernon township area. What if you have a hundred acres of farmland? What if you can&#039;t afford that? What if you don&#039;t have any children, and you couldn&#039;t care less about paying for Dr. Riggs&#039;s new gym?&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;According to Dr. Riggs himself: &lt;b&gt;Tough Noogies.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Okay, that&#039;s not a direct quote, but it would be easier for him to just say that. If you live in that northern Hancock county area that is Vernon Township, you &lt;b&gt;will&lt;/b&gt; have to pay those taxes, &lt;b&gt;without question&lt;/b&gt;. The expansion plans went through the school board with a vote of 3-1 in favor, without even questioning the taxpayers opinion. &lt;b&gt;Tough noogies, indeed&lt;/b&gt;. Dr. Riggs was so convinced that the plan would go through without problem that he didn&#039;t even make the effort to ask anyone their opinion. The plan was given with the voice of someone who has no uncertainty, no question about whether or not taxpayers will be willing to pay for it or not. What&#039;s worse is that &lt;b&gt;it worked&lt;/b&gt;. The football stadium was getting boring, the intermediate school was already collecting dust. Riggs was bored, and wanted some new project to think about.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;And what of those sad residents of Vernon Township who will have to pay for his new diversion? The residents, of which my parents are proud members, &lt;b&gt;will be forced&lt;/b&gt; to deal with this plan. Or will they? A small band of residents, a Rebel Alliance if you will, has risen up and declared a &lt;a href=&quot;http://dictionary.reference.com/search?q=remonstrance&quot; title=&quot;Definition&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;remonstrance&lt;/a&gt; on the evil Mt. Vernon Empire. A petition has gone around collecting signatures of people who don&#039;t want to pay an additional 85% in property taxes. The petition has a very good chance of getting enough signatures. Two distinct factions &lt;b title=&quot;Passive voice.  I know, mom!&quot;&gt;have formed&lt;/b&gt;. The members of the remonstrance, and their blue forms are facing off against the proponents of the plan, and their yellow forms. It is an epic struggle between the &quot;blue forms&quot; and the &quot;yellow forms.&quot; Needless to say, the &lt;b&gt;blue formers&lt;/b&gt; have a lot of strong information backing up their position. Like the Rebel Alliance of a long time ago, the blue formers just might win this war. I really hope that Riggs is shaking in his &quot;academic achievement&quot; boots, because he&#039;s next. I hope he doesn&#039;t drop his &lt;b&gt;beloved golden cross&lt;/b&gt; on his way out.&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt;Why am I so up at arms about this? After all, I did promise myself that I wouldn&#039;t concern myself with that place any more. I don&#039;t go there anymore, and don&#039;t pay any property taxes. So what&#039;s the problem? &lt;b&gt;My parents&lt;/b&gt;, though they have no more students to drag throught the gauntlet, &lt;b&gt;still have to pay for the construction&lt;/b&gt;. &lt;i title=&quot;For, um, books! Yeah, books!&quot;&gt;That is money that they could be giving me!&lt;/i&gt; Seriously, though, this goes so much farther than Fortville, Indiana. Mt. Vernon&#039;s construction plan brings a whole new moral dilema to the game. Far more important than whether or not to allow the &lt;b&gt;Ten Commandments&lt;/b&gt; in the classroom, far more important than capital punishment, is the concept of the business of public education. No longer does Mt. Vernon care about preparing students for the world, not that I really think they ever did. No, Riggs is far more concerned with &lt;b&gt;&quot;raising personal wealth achievement for himself.&quot;&lt;/b&gt; That is why I care, and why you should, too.  If this plan goes through, how many more schools will follow this example?&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;I know I&#039;m bitter. I know I went through Hell to fill Riggses&#039; wallet. I know that with the proper application of adjectives, a &lt;b&gt;web logger&lt;/b&gt; can make any subject look bad. Still, $1000 dollars a year for life is a large price to pay for a gratuitous gym. &lt;b&gt;You can&#039;t argue with that.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;For more information on the remonsterance, visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mvtaxpayers.org&quot;&gt;mvtaxpayers.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;If you doubt any of my facts, just hold the mouse on them and a tooltip will pop up telling you where I got the information.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;Still doubt me?  &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:smcgill@purdue.edu&quot; title=&quot;If you want to rid the &#039;net of false info, good luck.&quot;&gt;TOUGH NOOGIES!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Life is good.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s really refreshing to have people -- well, peers -- who really care about me.  Where I grew up, in school if you showed any sort of emotion at all, you were quickly tought that &quot;people do not behave like that.&quot;  Well, I am free from that, and I now have friends who truly care about me.  Friends I truly care about.  When I&#039;m in an unhappy mood now, someone will actually talk to me about what&#039;s bothering me.  My whole life, I always thought to myself, &quot;college is going to be so awesome,&quot; etc.  First semester, I wouldn&#039;t have agreed with it, but now I sure do.  This past couple months has been the best couple months of my life.  The only thing that could make this any better would be if Star Wars was coming out on my birthday again.  OH WAIT, IT IS!!!!!  Yeah, that totally r0xx0rz.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Seriously, though, the one real downside to this year is pretty blaringly obvious.  I really miss my parents.  They were always there for me.  I could have intelligent conversations with them, without fear of them bashing my ego against the wall.  I feel so bad about the fact that I haven&#039;t called them as much as I could have.  I think the reason I haven&#039;t been thinking about them very much is that if I started thinking about it, I would really begin to realize how much I really do miss them.  I miss eating breakfast with my Dad.  I miss talking to my Mom about school.  I miss playing &quot;trucks&quot; with my Dad.  I miss having Mom read books to me before I went to sleep.  I miss my Dad&#039;s infinite and artistic craftiness.  I miss my Mom&#039;s ability to write the perfect thing at any time.  Now I&#039;m starting to cry, see?&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Well, I will have to look forward to this summer, because I will be working with my Dad and his amazing artistic skills, and I will be able to have intelligent conversations with my Mom again.  Before I left, my Mom told me that I would be missing fresh eggs.  I do, Mom.  I do miss your chickens&#039; eggs.  I miss having eggs with every meal.  Even though at the time I was annoyed with your writings and your various schemes, I would give anything to be able to hear what you are working on right now.  Being away has really shown me how amazingly inteligent and wise you guys are.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I guess I&#039;m at a junction in my life.  I am starting to become more of a college student, a purely social individual.  At the same time, I am feeling pain from being torn from my parents and my childhood.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;What&#039;s my point?  It&#039;s actually pretty simple.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I love my wonderful new friends.  More importantly, I love my Mom and Dad.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;You can check out some information about some of my friends (paticularly the ones in my hall) at Lord Ontario&#039;s web site.  It&#039;s an irrelevant link. (on the left hand side of the screen)&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My family and I went to see &lt;i&gt;Robots&lt;/i&gt; last night.  It was really a lousy movie, if you must know.  I don&#039;t know why Newsweek would hail, &quot;the funniest movie of the year,&quot; because it really wasn&#039;t that funny.  Maybe it&#039;s just me, because I have a weird sense of humor.  I never laugh at the show &lt;i&gt;Family Guy&lt;/i&gt;, even when my friends around me are always cracking up.  Even still, comedy does not make a movie, not by any means.  I&#039;m going to compare this movie to the &lt;i&gt;Incredibles&lt;/i&gt;, which I don&#039;t agree with at all, but they started it (in their commercial), so they deserve it.  I don&#039;t think that they are in the same league, so it&#039;s hard to compare them.  &lt;i&gt;Robots&lt;/i&gt; is not anywhere near the nuance or pure creativity of &lt;I&gt;the Incredibles&lt;/i&gt;.  &lt;i&gt;The Incredibles&lt;/i&gt; is without at doubt the greatest animated movie of all time, in my opinion.  It just barely edges out &lt;i&gt;Monsters, Inc&lt;/i&gt;.  I even consider it to be one of the greatest movies ever made, since it hardly feels like an animation.  &lt;i&gt;Robots&lt;/i&gt;, on the other hand, although their commercial would say otherwise, is not a decent movie at all.  Why is that?  What makes the &lt;i&gt;Incredibles&lt;/i&gt; so much better than &lt;i&gt;Robots&lt;/i&gt;?  Absolutely everything.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Robots has a lousy, predictable script, stupid character development, and just bad planning.  While watching it, I felt like it was more of a series of short animations than a whole movie.  They threw in too many gags to have any sort of consistency in the characters.  Also, where Pixar somehow seems to succeed in every movie they have made, Robots just seems way too cluttered.  Pixar movies have a certain level of detail in every shot, but yet it never seems cluttered or overly complicated.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately for Robots, one of its biggest strengths is also what makes it a bad movie.  The animators went to great lengths to make it look spectacular, and indeed it does.  Every scene has outstanding technology, from the huge scale transportation system to the extremely detailed domino sequence.  The problem is that it just seems like the animators were showcasing the capabilities of whatever animation package they were using.  This is the computer animator in me coming out, and I could go on about this movie for a while.  I felt like I was at an expo, and some software company was showcasing their new physics system.  Each scene of the movie felt like a sepparate short animation showcasing a different capability.  The animators did things just because they could, not because it really helped the movie&#039;s plot at all  (not that there was a plot to help).&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I must say, though, that the design work, like the character models and the environments were extremely detailed and well done.  The voice acting was also top notch, but that&#039;s what you would expect when a company spends more on the actors and design then they spend on the script.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;As bad as Robots was, I will say that it was so much better than Shark Tale, or even Shrek, in my opinion.  I thought both of those movies were terrible.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;One important thing to say is this:  before Robots, the theatre showed the new trailor for Episode 3.  It&#039;s worth going just for that.  George Lucas has taken a lot of space-flak for his prequels, and I feel terrible about that.  I loved both Episode 1 and 2, and I&#039;m sure 3 will blow my socks off (along with my feet).  I am going to need to make a post about the prequels, because something needs to be said.  Stay tuned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I find myself lost.  Just absolutely lost.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;I can only try to regain control of my life.&lt;/p&gt;
			Here I am, just a man, one of oh so many.&lt;br /&gt;
				With coin in hand at this old wishing well.&lt;br /&gt;
				And I don&#039;t know if I believe in making wishes, but something has me saying, &lt;i&gt;only time will tell.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
				So I wish I was a breeze in summer. I&#039;d wrap around you; I&#039;d dance in your hair. And if for a moment you should chance to breathe me, I&#039;d carry your voice till it filled the air.&lt;br /&gt;

				&lt;br /&gt;
				Lately skies have me thinking about you.&lt;br /&gt;
				On open roads I hear your voice, I have to turn, &#039;cause not one face or story, not one single song of glory has ever won back my heart from you.&lt;br /&gt;
				&lt;br /&gt;
				I would I were a splinter of moonlight.&lt;br /&gt;
				I&#039;d come so softly, to fall on your bed.&lt;br /&gt;
				I would bring you a map of dreamland, and I&#039;d stay all night to watch o&#039;re your head.&lt;br /&gt;

				&lt;br /&gt;
				And if in dreams I was a ship in the water I would be sturdy, I would be sound.&lt;br /&gt;
				And I&#039;d sail over any sea or ocean to the harbour of your love where I would lay my anchor down.&lt;br /&gt;
				&lt;br /&gt;
				Lately skies have me thinking about you.&lt;br /&gt;
				On open roads I hear your voice, I have to turn, &#039;cause not one face or story, not one single song of glory has ever won back my heart from you.&lt;br /&gt;
				&lt;br /&gt;

				Well, here I am, just a man, one of oh so many.&lt;br /&gt;
				With empty hands, dreams in my eyes.&lt;br /&gt;
				And I&#039;m not sure, if dreams get answered, but until then, there&#039;s open roads and open skies.&lt;br /&gt;
				&lt;br /&gt;
				To tell the truth, no face or story, not one single song of glory has ever won back my heart from you.
				&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

				This song sums up everything pretty well.&lt;br /&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I know you won&#039;t probably ever see this.  Still, it would be nice if you did.  I know you think that I&#039;m just a foolish kid, blinded by my false impressions of you.  I just don&#039;t understand what you think I have wrong.  I have a million reasons why I love you, most of which I don&#039;t even know or understand.  I went there hoping to find something that would allow me let go, but I only found the opposite.  I lost track of what I want to do with myself.  I lost all purpose in my life.  Maybe things will settle down and I will be fine in a little bit, but as I walk along these open roads, not one single thing will ever make me forget what an amazing person you are, and no one will ever win my heart from you.  I don&#039;t feel like I was able to really tell you how I feel.  I have all these thoughts that I wanted to express, but I couldn&#039;t express them.  I wanted to tell you everything, but I couldn&#039;t put it to words.  I must have told you &quot;like&quot; or &quot;you know&quot; like 500 times, you know?  For a year, I would have given anything to be able to see you. Now, all I want is just to be able to never see you again.  As it is, I will have to find my way down there again to get another few minutes to try.  Another few minutes to try and express myself.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t know why I feel like this.  I don&#039;t know what to do.  Why do I always get the feeling like nobody really wants me around?  I wish I could spend the rest of my life in her arms.  Not because I love her, but because when she hugs me, for that moment, I stop feeling un-wanted.  Any time I am with people, a part of me constantly tells me that they don&#039;t want me there.  I wish I could spend the rest of my life hugging her.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;She was the one who told me that when I go to college I won&#039;t have a real home anymore.  Like everything she told me, it is profoundly true.  I&#039;m home for spring break, and I just feel like I am in the way.  I feel like I am breaking up everyone&#039;s routine.  Yet, I can&#039;t really call Purdue my home, especially now that I am having second thoughts about enrolling there.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I need to stop second guessing myself all the time.  I need to stop thinking that I am so inferior to everyone else.  I need to forget about her and move on.  Right?&lt;/p&gt;

				If you want to know why I love you so much, all you have to do is just give me a call.  You can&#039;t ever do that, though, can you?  I can&#039;t even be mad at you, because I understand and respect why you do everything you do.  I need to just stop thinking.&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;p&gt;I want the old days back, when I saw you every day and you laughed at my jokes even when you didn&#039;t immediately get them.&lt;/p&gt;

