data.text:
&lt;p&gt;Ok, I&#039;m sorry for not posting anything in a while, I&#039;ve had a lot of stuff to say but I&#039;ve been either too lazy or too busy to post.&lt;p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Click here to get the skinny on everything.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;It started two weeks ago.  We had to take out lofts down and turn them in on Thursday, April 28.  That was a big hassle, because we had (and by &quot;we&quot; I mean &quot;I&quot;) had to totally rearrange the room so that we could return our beds to the lofted position. Everything I moved just uncovered more piles of various filth. Huge piles of dust, piles of socks, piles of other random stuff. It was pretty disgusting, especially since most of it wasn&#039;t mine, and most especially because every pile had various foods and liquids in them. Chris Fancher and I played a small soccer match in the hall with an old piece of cheese stick that I found under Scott&#039;s desk. The cheesestick looked completely fine, but since it had been sitting under some socks for a couple weeks, it had gotten extremely hard. It was so hard that it hurt my toe when I kicked it without a shoe on. It skidded down the hall and pinged against the wall with a hard knock. We said a lot of words expressing our disgust at that.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I was able to get the room resituated, and with the help of most of the guys in the hall, we lofted the beds. Mission accomplished. We didn&#039;t have much time to relax, however, because we had finals that next week, and then we had to move out. I was scared about moving out, to be sure. Here are some pictures of the task that befell us: &lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/room.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy a bottle of water.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/roomthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/window.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy Winnie the Pooh.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/windowthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/mycloset.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy an Elephant.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/myclosetthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/scottcloset.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy some extremely old donuts.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/scottclosetthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			
&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/mydesk.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy disk 1.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/mydeskthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/scottsdesk.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I spy a white electrical plug.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/scottsdeskthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/p&gt;

			
			&lt;p&gt;We had a lot of work ahead of us, as you can see. Everything went well, though, and we were able to entertain the hall while we did it. They were all really eager to see how we would get all of that junk out of the room, but they weren&#039;t quick to help. The only help we got from them was Fred, and he only helped by taking a bunch of stuff that we didn&#039;t really want anymore. He took a pack of plastic spoons and plastic forks, some oatmeal creme pies, a half full bag of wal-mart brand cereal, a broken lavalamp, an old ethernet patch cable, and a bunch of other junk. See if you can find any of that in the pictures! (some of it cannot be seen).&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Here it is, a whole week later, and I still haven&#039;t unpacked yet, so my room at home is just about as cluttered. Oh well, I&#039;m used to it, right?&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My plan was just to work all summer, and make a bunch of money to buy some stuff for the room and have money to use at school next year. I was totally expecting, except for the movie coming out in a week, to have a really boring summer. However, I&#039;ve only been home a week and it&#039;s already shaping up to be one of the best summers ever. My parents gave me my birthday present early this year. Yeah, my birthday is also May 19 (Mr. Lucas must have known, so he decided to give me a present. What a nice guy!). So what did I get for my 19th birthday? Well, since you are impatient you&#039;ve probably already clicked the link below and found out for yourself. Yes, my parents gave me a Darth Vader costume for my 19th birthday. &lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/jumpsuit.jpg&quot; title=&quot;He&#039;s not so scary with just the jumpsuit on.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/jumpsuitthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/jumpsuit2.jpg&quot; title=&quot;He&#039;s not so scary with just the jumpsuit on.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/jumpsuit2thumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/jumpsuit3.jpg&quot; title=&quot;He&#039;s not so scary with just the jumpsuit on.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/jumpsuit3thumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/jumpsuit4.jpg&quot; title=&quot;He&#039;s not so scary with just the jumpsuit on.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/jumpsuit4thumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/maskoff.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I fill it out, don&#039;t I?&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/maskoffthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/sidevader.jpg&quot; title=&quot;What a dork.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/sidevaderthumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/chokeaili.jpg&quot; title=&quot;Episode 3 Spoiler.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/chokeailithumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/jointhedarkside.jpg&quot; title=&quot;Join me and we can rule the galaxy.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/jointhedarksidethumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;a href=&quot;../assets/images/vader/family.jpg&quot; title=&quot;I&#039;m not wearing any shoes. I&#039;m tall.&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/thumbs/familythumb.jpg&quot; &gt;&lt;/a&gt;

			&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;p&gt;Yeah, how nerdy is that? It&#039;s pretty nerdy, really. If you ask me, anyway. Pretty damn nerdy. Well, anyway, that&#039;s a pretty cool thing. I just might be one of the only 19 year old boys who would be excited to get a Darth Vader costume for his birthday. I will be making various appearances across Greenfield, Indiana on the day of the movie, so that&#039;s going to be super fun.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;My parents just got a cable internet connection in early March, so for the first time ever, I have the internet in my bedroom. It&#039;s really surreal to think that I have the entire world at my fingertips right here. I&#039;ve never had that here before. I am typing this whole thing right in my bedroom. I&#039;ve never been this connected to my friends. I&#039;ve never had this many friends to talk to all at once, either. It&#039;s crazy for me. I thought this summer would be boring, but I&#039;m experiencing so many new things. Really wonderful things that have happened to me in the last couple weeks.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s surreal for me, too, to think that this could be the last time I will spend a prolonged time living with my parents. I could quite possibly have an internship in California next summer which would mean that I would have to move there. If anything, my parents are seriously looking at new property with the thought that they would be moving, which means that this will probably be the last time I will be living in the house that I have lived in my whole life. It feels like I&#039;m careening along a road, and the mountains I see just ahead of me are the many ways my life will soon change. The mountains aren&#039;t ahead of me, though. I&#039;m careening along a mountain road, with mountains all around me. I was talking to a friend the other day, and she told me that I have changed so much in the two months that she has known me. I think it&#039;s true. It&#039;s ok, though. I&#039;ve gotten used to mountain climbing. I&#039;ve gone on a hundred fountain runs since I&#039;ve been home. A hundred times, I&#039;ve climbed those mountains. That&#039;s just since I&#039;ve been home. I have so many mountains yet to climb, though.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;I need to start saving my money, though. I want to purchase most of the following items before next year:&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;

					&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Digital Camera&lt;/b&gt; - I don&#039;t need a top of the line one, but 4 or 5 megapixels would be cool.&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cellular Telephone&lt;/b&gt; - I still want one, although when I get one I&#039;ll probably almost never use it.&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;High Definition Television&lt;/b&gt; - This is for the room next year.  Just a basic one.&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;New Personal Data Assistant&lt;/b&gt; - Yeah, I&#039;m going to retire the ol&#039; Ipaq that my Dad gave me recently.  It doesn&#039;t give me the features that I really need (want).&lt;/li&gt;

				&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, I&#039;ve been talking about it for some time.  I want a new website.  I need to redesign a new website.  It will happen, and it will happen soon, so don&#039;t worry. Here are some wicked cool features you can look forward too:&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;PHP scripting&lt;/b&gt; - Nobody knows what it really stands for, but it kicks ass, so I&#039;m using it.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;NO FRAMES&lt;/b&gt; - Everyone hates frames, especially the web designers who have to wade through the billions of files that they create.&lt;/li&gt;

			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Easy Comment system&lt;/b&gt; - I don&#039;t think anyone has actually tried, but all over the site I have little comment links.  They don&#039;t work, in case you haven&#039;t noticed.  With PHP I can change that!&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;More symbols&lt;/b&gt; - I will spam my symbol all over the place, even more than I already have!&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;No Splash page&lt;/b&gt; - I&#039;m getting rid of the stupid page that just says &quot;ENTER&quot; on it.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Easier Navigation&lt;/b&gt; - The menu will be easier to use, and I&#039;m turning the portfolio into a sepparate site.&lt;/li&gt;

			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;More stuff of the moment&lt;/b&gt; - I&#039;ll have a whole slew of &quot;*blank* of the moment&quot; stuff.  Right now I just have a joke and a poem of the moment.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Better look&lt;/b&gt; - I&#039;m bored with my current look, and I hope you are too because it&#039;s changing.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;More pictures&lt;/b&gt; - I&#039;ve tried to put as many pictures as I could into this site, but I&#039;m going to have even more once I have my own digital camera to take them with.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Higher compatibility&lt;/b&gt; - the new site will work equally perfect on any browser you view it with (provided it is up to date).  I still believe that Firefox is the &lt;b&gt;BEST&lt;/b&gt; browser ever, but a lot of people use Internet Explorer too.&lt;/li&gt;

			&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;And much much more!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;/ul&gt;
			
			&lt;p&gt;I created this site, as you may know, mostly as a way to stay in touch with my parents.  Since I am living with them now, I&#039;ve pretty much lost 90% of my audience.  I never really thought many people actually read what I put up here, and there was little proof to change my mind. However, if you Google &quot;Shauvon,&quot; the first result you will get is this very site. I think that will get me a lot more traffic, so I need to have something worth looking at when they get here. (by the way, for those of you who actually know what I&#039;m talking about, the phrase &quot;super cramming power&quot; is still NOT on google) So although I don&#039;t think I have any audience at all, I will still redesign the site. One, I need something to do and to think about. Two, I want to make my site better than &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ontariosuave.com&quot; title=&quot;A very good site&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Cameron Marston&lt;/a&gt;&#039;s. And C, I want to make things easier for me to update, so that I have to do less work. Keep in touch, and email me if you have any suggestions. (I only got one comment on the name of the site, from Cameron himself, and he told me to make it &quot;noteverystudent.com&quot;) My hopes are slim that I will get any suggestions, though.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;And now, the phrase everyone&#039;s been waiting for: &lt;/p&gt;

