data.text:
&lt;p&gt;I finally had some time to sit down and work out a couple things with the site.  First of all, I finally fixed the &quot;About Me&quot; page.  It has a scrolling marquee that is supposed to say what I am currently doing, but it used to just say that I&#039;m not doing anything.  Well, I fixed it, so now if I am doing something (a rare occasion), it will say.  I will put big occasions and appointments and things there, so you can always check to see if anything is going on.  Or for you stalkers out there, you can easily see where I am at a given moment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, you might notice a series of letters up above the site title.  That is the latest updates ticker, and it will list the six most recent updates to the site.  It cycles every eight seconds.  This will make things easier for viewers, because all you have to do is click that text and it will take you straight to whatever update it is describing.  Neat?  Yes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Stay tuned for further updates.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m switching majors to Theatre.  It will be official pretty soon, and that makes a lot of changes in my life.  I don&#039;t know if I want to get that internship at LucasArts anymore.  Right now, I&#039;m thinking that this summer I will do something completely new and exciting.  I want to be a bartender or a DJ at some club.  I probably won&#039;t have much to choose from in Indianapolis, however.  We&#039;ll see what happens.  I&#039;ll probably end up getting a day job somewhere and then working nights at Comedy Sportz, if my sister can get me in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The world needs more things with the acronym &quot;CS&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just thought I would give a little update about the group project that I was in for CGT211.  My good friend &lt;a href=http://www.ontariosuave.com&gt;Extra Cameron, the Happy Canadian&lt;/a&gt; was also in the group.  The project was to create pre-production materials for a movie / video / whatever of our choice.  Extra Cameron, in a stroke of genius, decided that we should design a video for the Death Cab For Cutie song, &lt;i&gt;What Sarah Said&lt;/i&gt;, from their new album.  The song is hella depressing, so I won&#039;t go into huge detail about it.  Just click the link below to get all the scoopage on said project.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Yes, this link right here.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;What is pre-production, you ask?  Well, we were to design all of the aspects of the video, which according to Kellen Maicher, the godlike professor, boils down to Characters, Environments, and Props.  Extra Cameron designed a couple characters, the amazing Tyler Kupferer did another couple characters, Samantha the Senior designed the props and things, and Slick Stephen worked on one of the main environments.  (I just made those knick names up)  The song centers around a hospital (in that the entire thing takes place there).  Therefore, the environment was a hospital, the characters were patients and nurses, and the extra things were stuff like exit signs, coke machines, coffee cups, etcetera.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My part of the project was to do a couple of the environments.  For the last 4 summers, I&#039;ve been working at an architecture firm previsualizing environments, so I figured it would be pretty easy for me to do a couple hospital renderings.  The requirements of the project stated that we had to create a &lt;a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raster_graphics&gt;raster image&lt;/a&gt;.  There were many requirements about what the images was supposed to be like, but it didn&#039;t say anything about what program was to be used to create the image.  It&#039;s theoretically an Adobe Photoshop class, but I thought it was rediculous to render an environment in Photoshop, so I used 3d Studio Max.  Yeah, I cheated a little bit.  It&#039;s a raster image that fits every requirement for the project, so there is nothing wrong with it.  &lt;a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kobayashi_Maru class=black&gt;I&#039;m just like Captain Kirk.  &quot;I don&#039;t like to lose.&quot;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, here are my images:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, I had do do one of the hallways of the hospital, complete with rooms (albeit empty).  Several people have thought that the first one is a photograph.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=center&gt;&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/hallway.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/hallwaythumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/room0249.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/room0249thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sign at the end of the hallway points in the various directions for the Cardiology, Pulminology, Out Patient, ICU, and CGT 211 Student wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another section that I had to do was the waiting room.  I went ahead and did the area outside of the waiting room, too, because I love that reflective floor.  I designed those light fixtures because I saw them somewhere and I thought they looked cool.  I wanted to have as many harsh shadows as possible, to heighten the tension and depressing . . . ness of it all.  I think I saw those lights in a mexican restaurant somewhere.  Strange choice for mexican restaurant, but excellent choice for depressing waiting room.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=center&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0001.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0001thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0002.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0002thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0003.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0003thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0005.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/waiting_room0005thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is nothing behind the curtains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And finally, I was in charge of the outside of the hospital, which meant that I had to design an entire hospital complex, parking garage and all.  (don&#039;t let me fool you, I really enjoyed it)  You may notice several things.  It is raining.  There are no windows on the actual hospital (this is because the shot in the video is from above, zooming away from the guy sitting on the ground, so you never see the hospital walls).  The parking garage only has lights on the first row of columns (it already took about 10 minutes to render one frame, I didn&#039;t want to make it take any longer by doubling the lights).  Finally, you might notice the &lt;a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z-buffer&gt;z-buffer&lt;/a&gt; error on the large windows of the diagonal wall in the image named &quot;ground0005.png&quot; (some of the windows don&#039;t display because they are so close to the surface of the wall, and I was too lazy to fix it).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=center&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/sweep0003.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/sweep0003thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/sweep0008.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/sweep0008thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/ground0005.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/ground0005thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/ground0006.png&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/project/ground0006thumb.jpg /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ambulance is just two white boxes with the word &quot;Wambulance&quot; printed all over it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now for the technical info.  Let me just get this out of the way, so I can feel special for knowing so many big words.  You can skip to the next paragraph if you don&#039;t want to read the mumbo jumbo.  Stick with me, though, because the ending is really good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The two scenes were rendered in 3d studio max 7, using radiosity calculations and photometric lights.  The hallway scene and the waiting room are connected together.  All of the textures were created from scratch in Adobe Photoshop, with the sole exception being the magazine covers in the waiting room.  The floor reflection was achieved using a raytraced material.  All of the objects were modeled with simple primitives.  The outdoor scene contains a total of 144 lights, and the hallway / waiting room contains 39.  I think that about does it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although I was afraid that I would get in trouble for not using photoshop to render the scenes, they didn&#039;t seem to care at all.  We turned in our project and awaited the presentations.  This week, on Monday and Tuesday, every group had 5 minutes to present their work, which included at least two pieces per group member, and around 100 storyboards.  Five minutes was undoubtedly not enough time.  Anyway, our group, which was called Team Steel Blue, by the way, decided that we should make a video for our presentation, instead of making some stupid powerpoint presentation or something.  Good old Tyler worked up a five minute video a la VH1&#039;s &lt;i&gt;Behind the Music&lt;/i&gt;.  Neeless to say, we &lt;a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Owned class=black&gt;owned&lt;/a&gt; everyone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We all got an email from Professor Maicher yesterday, which explains how awesome we are.  Apparently he sent a copy to several other professors, who all thought it was great.  Although Maicher wants to teach us about the real professional world, he doesn&#039;t seem to have any problem with distributing our creative property.  It&#039;s no big deal, because it&#039;s definitely awesome enough to want to show everyone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only one group in the class will earn an A on this project, whith everyone else geting a B or lower.  I&#039;ll be sure to post the grade that we got, but judging from the other presentations, I don&#039;t think there&#039;s much competition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m happy to say that I have a copy of the video for your viewing pleasure.  Feel free to distribute it all you want, but it would be nice if you give me an email so I can give Tyler an email asking to use it.  The credit for all the filming and editing goes to Tyler, who is definitely one of the greatest minds of our generation.  We all worked really hard on this project, so everyone take a look at &lt;i&gt;211: Behind the Project&lt;/i&gt;.  It&#039;s in Windows Media format, and for that I appologize.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=../assets/images/project/steelbluepresentation.wmv&gt;Team Steel Blue:  Behind the Project (57.6 MB)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m pretty much just making sure that my new image upload system works correctly.  I&#039;m going to be home most of next week for Thanksgiving, so I want to be able to make posts and upload images from home, which I should be able to do.  I think the images work pretty well.  If you want, I&#039;ll tell you what we did last night.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Ok, Shauvon, tell me about last night.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td rowspan=2 valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I spent all day yesterday working on a little side project I have going.  I&#039;ve been wanting to render a space scene for a while now, so I started playing around with 3d Studio on Friday.  I re-developed my intimate relationship with 3ds while working on the &lt;a href=../content/news.php?post=00093&gt;211 project&lt;/a&gt;.  I quickly worked up a nice planet + ring scene, and I started modelling a space fighter.  I made both of them up as I went, and they are turning out pretty well.  I still have to skin the fighter, and insert a couple of them into the planet.  I&#039;m hoping I&#039;ll have some free time at home next week to work on that some more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/unsortable/planet.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/unsortable/fighter.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anyway, all day yesterday I was switching between working on the space fighter and playing &lt;i&gt;Quake 4&lt;/i&gt;, which really redeems itsself well in the later levels.  Neal, Cameron, and Chris came back pretty late in the day (around 7) because they went to Bloomington for the football game.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20055.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was surfing the internet for information about building a media center PC (I really want to build one), and Neal came in to the room with a big jug of orange juice.  He locked the door, and went into the other room.  I was confused about what they were doing in there, but I was more interested in &lt;a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turion_64 class=black&gt;AMD Turion 64&lt;/a&gt; processors, so I didn&#039;t really think about it too much.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My fingers slid across the computer, pressing &quot;flag&quot; and &quot;L&quot; to lock my computer, so nobody finds my collection of Star Trek fan fiction.  I journeyed over into the other room, and found the four guys (Mike Davis had joined them at this point) sitting around drinking orange juice.  They had apparently aquired some sort of special tonic which they were mixing with the juice.  It seems that they didn&#039;t want anyone else asking to have some of their orange juice, so Neal locked the door to keep the juice-hounds out.  By the time I came into the room, half of the 1.75 litre bottle of tonic was finished.  They must have been worried about someone finding out about something, because the bottle had quite a bit of proof in it.  I don&#039;t like anything without Tang or Dr. Pepper in it, so I didn&#039;t try any of their orange juice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris took what was left of our koolaide and mixed it with his juice.  I know the picture is of Neal, but it was Chris who made the drink.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20056.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20057.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20024.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everyone started discussing various topics.  One main point of discussion was the trip to Bloomington, in which they found Chris&#039;s brother&#039;s girlfriend to be somewhat unsavory.  Chris mentioned that he thought his brother&#039;s girlfriend was a &quot;chief example of someone who needs to continue to develop her social skills and ability to deal with guests.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20065.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He was very firm and coherant in his arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20041.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle rowspan=2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal found it necessary to reiterate how much orange juice he drank, explaining how many &quot;friends&quot; he had inside him.  Chris ate his steak sandwich that he purchased in Bloomington.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20086.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20087.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, Cameron and Mike Davis were having a discussion.  Cameron likes to discuss all sorts of things sometimes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20058.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron wanted to make sure that I understood what he was saying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20022.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=5&gt;
&lt;div style=&#039;text-align: center&#039;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Neal&#039;s Adventure&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal decided to call his sister, who has been living in the Ukraine for the past couple years.  He sure talked to her for quite a while.  I couldn&#039;t hear what she was saying, but I&#039;m sure she was very interested to hear about how many friends Neal had ingested.  Neal explained to her that I was taking pictures of him.  She must have been telling him a really funny joke, because he couldn&#039;t seem to stop laughing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal was somewhat alarmed that I had a picture of the Blue Man Group on the front of my shirt.  He made several comments about the blue men on my chest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t know what his sister was talking to him about, but he kept telling her that he was focused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20006.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20017.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20033.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20011.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20034.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal was apparently annoyed with me taking pictures of him, and he expressed his feelings by biting my camera.  I&#039;m not sure what his sister thought about that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20029.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since the camera didn&#039;t satiate his appetite, he looked around for more food.  Chris&#039;s sandwich came with several sweet pickles, which Neal was quite partial to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20079.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course, the pickles made his hands dirty, so he had to wash them off.  He found the toilet more than adequate for the task.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20073.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stomach full and hands clean, he was able to go back to talking to his Sister.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20069.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When he finished talking to his sister, Neal turned to the other residents of our hall for topics of discussion.  Neal&#039;s neighbor was wearing an orange hat, which must have reminded Neal of one of his least favorite football teams.  Neal told him that orange was one of his least favorite colors.  I think Neal expressed his arguments pretty well, and the other guy had a hard time working up any sort of response.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20094.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20082.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He obviously couldn&#039;t come up with any response for Neal&#039;s well thought out arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal83cropped.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal was getting pretty worked up, though, and I was afraid that he was going to start a fight.  He repeatedly expressed his wishes to damage the poor guy&#039;s various bones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20084.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortunately Neal decided not to pursue the matter any further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20081.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron and Barry were discussing something now, I believe this time Cameron was discussing some kind of music.  Cameron had just returned from the third floor, where he was hanging out with some random people who he ran into.  Cameron decided that he was going to bring the rest of us up to the third floor to meet his new friends.  This brought about some more discussion.  Chris mentioned that one of the girls they had seen was rather attractive.  Cameron was able to persuade us to go up to the third floor with him.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20161.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20163.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20165.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron was never able to find his friend&#039;s room.  Meredith is very hard to navigate, so it&#039;s no suprise that we couldn&#039;t find our way around the labyrinth.  Cameron finally entered a room.  We asked him if these were the people he met earlier, and he said no.  They were nice anyway, and they talked with Cameron for a while.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20118.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neal turned to me and mentioned something about how nice these people were.  It was cerainly nice of them to let us hang out in their room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20130.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then he made another phone call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20128.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Next we decided to go visit Scott, who also lives on the third floor of Meredith.  It was a long walk down the hall to his room.  Neal had to stop in the shower room on the way there and ask everyone what there names were.  Cameron had to lay down and rest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eventually we made it to Scott&#039;s room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20113.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20114.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20167.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Scott was very happy to see us.  He never actually said that, but I&#039;m pretty sure it was understood.  His room is very small.  Realtors call it cozy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20169.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron tried his hand at one of Scott&#039;s computer games,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20172.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris was very suprized by something,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20176.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=middle&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and Neal made another phone call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20174.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chris told Scott all about his brother&#039;s girlfriend and her indadequate social skills.  Scott was very sympathetic.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20177.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We said goodbye to Scott and went on our way.  Scott was concerned that we were making too much noise, and he told us that we should be quieter.  Good old Scott is always helping out.  It was very nice of him.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20179.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All this journeying around Meredith was pretty hard for all of us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20182.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both Cameron and Neal had a hard time getting back to my room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20137.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron almost went to the wrong floor.  I live on the first floor, and the second floor is all girls.  He would have been very embarrassed if we hadn&#039;t stopped him.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20183.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;div style=&#039;text-align: center&#039;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cameron&#039;s Adventure&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron and I were both pretty tired from all of our journeys around the building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20184.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron was very interested in a poker game that was going on in the study room.  The poker players weren&#039;t as enthusiastic about him as he was about them.  I finally peeled him away from the glass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20186.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He saw some people outside in front of the lobby, so he wanted to investigate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20187.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top rowspan=2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It turns out that it was a group of young Purdue students from India.  Cameron introduced himself, and started to discuss lots of important issues with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He made it clear that he is actually from Canada, and he hates Americans.  He also made it clear that he hates George Bush.  He learned everyone&#039;s name, and how to pronounce them correctly.  It was clearly a long day for Cameron, because he was having trouble pronouncing their names.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20190.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20206.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They all sat on the sidewalk, and became more culturally aware.  Cameron showed everyone how to sit &quot;Indian style.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20197.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron learned a lot about his new friends and their culture.  Look how much more culturally aware he looks in this picture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20209.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He also made a lot of friends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20213.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cameron talked to his new friends for a long time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20193.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was getting pretty cold outside in the wind, so I told Cameron that I was going back to my room.  He stayed and hung out with his new friends for a while.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20195.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td valign=top&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are 55 pictures here, and this is the only one I am in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src=../assets/images/drunk/neal%20216.jpg /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, I would say that the image uploading system is working pretty well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I sure am glad that I go to college, because I get to have such interesting and enlightening nights like last night.  I get to hang around with friends discussing various intellectual topics in a distinguished and scholarly manor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ok, the DSE needs to be stopped.  I don&#039;t know what it is, but somebody really needs to start reading these emails.  I just got one with the following subject:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;DSE_Info:  Come to Speed Dating to Help St. Jude Children&#039;s Research Hospital&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What does that even mean?  I don&#039;t want to speed date children.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

