&lt;p&gt;Jim Davis is a comic genius.  His strip, &lt;i&gt;Garfield&lt;/i&gt; isn&#039;t really very funny anymore.  &lt;b&gt;To the untrained eye!&lt;/b&gt;  He obvously knew that to branch off into more cerebral comedy would kill his strip, so he kept it somewhat normal.  However, if you simply remove all of Garfield&#039;s thought bubbles, it becomes one of the funniest comic strips to ever grace the newspaper.  Find out for yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
