&lt;p&gt;Three days until I get my first cell phone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will add more pictures of my hair growing soon, just be patient.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Everyone needs to see this movie.  I urge you all, as citizens of Earth (and probably the United States), to learn about the current crisis we are faced with.  It isn&#039;t war.  It isn&#039;t oil.  It isn&#039;t the current administration.  It isn&#039;t rising gas prices.  It isn&#039;t the corporations taking over.  It isn&#039;t Apple.  It isn&#039;t Microsoft.  It isn&#039;t nuclear war.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This crisis is &lt;b&gt;global warming&lt;/b&gt;.  I know, I know, global warming has been about as much of a concern as a plague of locusts, and nobody really cares.  I&#039;m telling you, though, it&#039;s important, and you need to see just how much.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is my opinion that Al Gore would have been the igreatest president of all time, were he elected in 2000 (or had the republicans not stolen the election, however the case might be).  He has an extremely important message.  It&#039;s very disappointing that people today are so controlled by politics that they refuse to see his message.  Please, for your own sake, look past your blind devotion for just 100 minutes and listen to what he has to say.  If you don&#039;t, there is a very good chance that hundreds of millions of people will die.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The film is &lt;i&gt;An Inconvenient Truth&lt;/i&gt;, out now in theatres across the country.  You can see a list of the theatres the film is playing at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.climatecrisis.net/findatheater/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.climatecrisis.net&quot;&gt;www.climatecrisis.net&lt;/a&gt; for more information about how you can save the world.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Feel free to tell me why I might be wrong here.  I would love to discuss it.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve seen &lt;i&gt;Pirates of the Carribean: Dead Man&#039;s Chest&lt;/i&gt; twice now.  It&#039;s rather good.  If anybody wants to see it, let me know and I&#039;ll go with you.  I&#039;ve been wanting to see it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;again&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

