data.text:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Happy aniversary!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;denyconformity.com has achieved the highest honor it could have hoped for.  Rob Cockerham, the owner-operator of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cockeyed.com&quot;&gt;www.cockeyed.com&lt;/a&gt;, has commented on one of my posts.  The post is &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/content/news.php?post=00146&quot;&gt;&quot;Shauron&#039;s name adventures&quot;&lt;/a&gt;, and his comment shines like a beacon of hope for the rest of my posts to strive for.  Cockeyed.com is totally one of the greatest websites in the tubes today (it&#039;s actually sixth-best, according to the site itsself).  Since denyconformity.com&#039;s creation, one year ago, twenty five people have made one hundred fourty six comments. (counting all of the anonymous comments as one person).  I am currently the leader, with fourty-nine comments.  Anonymous Contributor is second, with fourty.  Cameron Marston (a.k.a. Lord Ontario) is in distant third with thirteen comments (but he cheated by splitting his long-winded comments into several parts).  Both my Mom and my sister, Aili, have made twelve, and Andrew Monkey has made ten.  The rest of the comments were made by Ben, Missy, Chris, Neal, Adam, Bob, Scott, Dayna, Mike, Barry, Peter, Nikkie, Will, Melody, Judy, Maya, Meg, Aaron, and Rob.  Everyone wish this site the best of luck in its second year in the tubes!&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m in Purdue&#039;s production of &lt;i&gt;Richard III&lt;/i&gt;, and I need to submit a bio for the program or whatever.  If anyone out there isn&#039;t familiar with bios, they&#039;re stupid and pointless little paragraphs that people write about themselves.  I despise them for several reasons.  They always feel like I&#039;m showing off, I don&#039;t like writing something so mundane, and I never know what to say.  I&#039;m supposed to turn a bio in today, so I&#039;m going to see what I can do.  Humor me, if you will, and I will try a few things out here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, the classic, boring, stupid, meaningless, informative bio.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;Shauvon McGill is a Junior majoring in theatre.  This is his second semester in the department, and his third production at Purdue.  Shauvon came to Purdue to study computer graphics technology, but he switched to theatre because he prefers the security of modern professional theatre.  Shauvon wants to thank his parents, his friend Scott, his role model Rob Cockerham, and of course, Ina Garten.&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Boring.  Let&#039;s spice it up a little bit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;Shauvon McGill is and always has been composed entirely of a new type of spatial plasma which has yet to be discovered by the scientific community.  Many years ago, several stars collided in deep space.  The mass of the two stars collected together, creating this new substance and launching it at the planet Earth.  The mass landed on the surface of the planet and cooled to form the body of Shauvon McGill.  A reclusive mad scientist found the lifeless body and took it to his lab to study.  A few years later, the mad scientist was working on an experiment when something went terribly wrong.  The scientist was killed, but his mind was mysteriously transported to the plasma body.  He gave up his scientific career and decided to study theatre at Purdue University.  This is his third show.&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Much more interesting, no?  A couple weeks ago, I wrote a bio for Andrew Preston (I&#039;m much more comfortable writing bios about someone besides me) for the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thecrazymonkeys.com&quot;&gt;Crazy Monkeys website&lt;/a&gt;.  It turned out pretty sweet.  I could just steal that back and change his name to mine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;Many years ago, for a brief moment in time, the universe was perfectly aligned to a particular position that only occurs once every two hundred million billion years.  Scientists call this event the cosmic rocking, and it is a phenomena that most humans were completely unaware of.  In fact, only a select few even know that the cosmic event exists.  However, that cosmic event is the most important thing that will ever happen.  At that precise moment, almost twenty five years ago, at the instantaneous event when every single body in the entire universe was perfectly aligned, a baby was born on a small planet in the Milky Way Galaxy.  That planet was Earth.  Some believe that the baby was imbued with the energies of the entire universe, and some say that it was an emissary sent from the gods to teach us to be at peace with one another.  Whatever the case, everyone knew that this child was special.  The child soon found powers beyond those of any normal human.  Soon, the child advanced beyond every other child, every teacher, and even those considered to be superior human beings.  Scientists from all over the planet came to study this being, and discover what gave it these amazing powers.  Not a single human being could discover what caused this creature to be so superior.  All of the knowledge, the documentation, and the studies meant nothing.  All of human logic was useless.  The being&#039;s powers were beyond even human imagination, which was always thought to be infinite in its abilities.  This being could rock.  It rocked hard, and it rocked fast.  The being could rock harder and faster than anything that ever existed in the history of the universe.  The world was stunned, for the universe had created the ultimate being.  This being is the pinnacle of existence.  This being is Shauvon McGill.&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;They&lt;/b&gt; probably won&#039;t let me submit that, though.  It&#039;s too &quot;out there&quot; for them.  What a bunch of prudes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But what if I submit a bio that is written about the future instead of the past?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;Shauvon McGill will graduate from Purdue University in three years.  After failing to do anything with his theatre degree, he will spend six years living in his parent&#039;s house, playing computer games and completing freelance web design projects to pay for more computer games.  At the age of 29, Shauvon will finally meet the girl of his dreams, and move out of his parents house.  Shauvon will spend the next six years moving around the world with his girlfriend, who is a competitive pole-vaulter.  Shauvon will then be contacted by an old friend of his who needs a writer for a sketch comedy show.  Shauvon will spend the next twenty seven years writing sketch comedy and eventually comedic films.  Shauvon wants to thank his parents, his friend Scott, and of course, Ina Garten.&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m just not feeling very attached to any of these.  Here is what I am going to do.  The other night, my friend Lauren Sivak had a dream that she submitted her bio, and the department changed it to &quot;Cast, beer, friends, life.&quot;  She was upset, because she doesn&#039;t even drink beer.  The graduate students told her that they can change her bio however they want, and she can&#039;t do anything about it.  Finally, she saw me.  I was upset about my bio, as well.  The department simply changed mine to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;Rivargo . . . ?&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s short, it&#039;s sweet, it&#039;s mysterious.  There&#039;s no way they will let me use it, but it&#039;s worth a shot.  It will make my year if they put that in the program.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wish me luck.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or, &lt;b&gt;Shauvon and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; get taken by an old crippled lady.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			

&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/curse/lookoutzoomed.JPG&quot; class=&quot;weekly&quot; /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Do you want to go to Goodwill?&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; Monkey said.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;That&#039;s the second time someone has asked me that today.&quot; I responded.  &quot;And the first time I will say &#039;yes.&#039;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Off we went, to the Goodwill store on the other side of town.  Little did we know that this trip would&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;font-size: 30px; color: red&quot;&gt;CHANGE OUR LIVES FOREVER!!!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;So, why do you have a coffin in the back of your car?&quot; I asked &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;, wondering why he had a coffin in the back of his car.  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; did, in fact, have a coffin in the back of his car, which confused me a little bit.  He just said, &quot;I don&#039;t know,&quot; and we climbed in and went off to Goodwill.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A few minutes later, our conversation about robots came to a close and my thoughts returned once again to the coffin in the back of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;&#039;s car.  It was a large wooden crate, about four feet wide and six feet tall.  It was predominantly plywood, and a few marks on the sides let us know which was was up.  Although the ability to quickly find up is a good thing to have when driving in your car, the presence of a large plywood coffin is not.  &quot;So, why &lt;i&gt;do&lt;/i&gt; you have a coffin in your car?&quot;  I asked again.  I&#039;m pretty sure the emphasis on the word &#039;do&#039; worked exactly the way I hoped, because it let &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; know that I meant business.  He told me what happened.  I don&#039;t think he was lying, because if he was, he would have come up with a much better story.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;He had apparently been driving home from work and noticed this large wooden crate sitting in the alley behind the coffee shop where he works, quietly letting passers by know which way was up.  He didn&#039;t even think twice about it because &lt;b&gt;when you see a wooden crate in an alley behind the coffee shop where you work you can&#039;t waste any time thinking about what you would do with it just pick it up and come up with something later.&lt;/b&gt;  A simmilar thing happened to us when we saw a &quot;One Way&quot; sign laying in the grass behind Jimmy Johns.  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; didn&#039;t have his car at the time, and we didn&#039;t want to walk down State Street holding a &quot;One Way&quot; sign.  I wish we had gotten it, because then we could start a collection of things that point out other things.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;../assets/images/curse/box.JPG&quot; class=&quot;weekly&quot; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Later, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; would use the box to stand in.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;For those of you wondering when we would get to the gypsy&#039;s organ, your time has come at last.&lt;/b&gt;  Three fourths of the way to the Goodwill store, we had to stop at a stoplight behind a few other vehicles.  &lt;i&gt;Act of fate A: if we had been just a few minutes earlier or later, we wouldn&#039;t have been stopped where we were, and the following would not have happened.&lt;/i&gt;  I looked to my right, and I saw a house.  The sign in front said, &quot;ESP Readings: Open.&quot;    &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Do you want to get an ESP reading?&quot; I asked &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;What?&quot; He responded, confused.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Do you want a sweet organ?&quot; I asked &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;What?&quot; He responded, amazed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For you see, in front of the ESP lady&#039;s house sat a sweet organ.  It was big, it was made of wood, and it had two rows of keys.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Look at that sweet organ.&quot; I suggested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Woah, that &lt;i&gt;is&lt;/i&gt; a sweet organ.&quot; He confirmed.  His emphasis of the word &quot;is&quot; showed that he meant business.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The traffic moved ahead of us, and we had to leave the organ behind, for the moment.  We discussed the possibilities of purchasing the organ, and we debated the reason for the organ&#039;s exterior home.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The fact that it&#039;s sitting outside shows that it&#039;s for sale, right?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;You would think so, but there was no sign.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Well, the fact that there is no sign could mean that it&#039;s free.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I hate it when people say that.  Just because there is no sign doesn&#039;t mean that it&#039;s free.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I wasn&#039;t saying that, I was honestly wondering.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I don&#039;t know, maybe it&#039;s just sitting there.  It was back away from the sidewalk, so it might just live there.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Well, it wouldn&#039;t hurt to go in and inquire.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I don&#039;t even know how to play keyboard instruments.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;This is a perfect opportunity to learn.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We had arrived at Goodwill.  Shopping at Goodwill is always a suprise.  You never know what you&#039;re going to get.  I ended up finding a weird felt clock, a new swiss army knife to keep in my pocket, and two Lego sets (I know the risks involved with buying used Lego sets, but I thought it was worth it).  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; got a couple spatulas, an ice cream scoop, and two crazy lightbulbs.  This next part is pretty good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; checked out ahead of me.  As he walked up to the counter, the very cute girl standing behind the register commented on &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;&#039;s shirt (it was a Velvet Underground tshirt).  The connection was made.  Andrew looked at me and gave me a less than subtle wink.  It turns out that the girl was a senior in high school, which quickly scared &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; away.  He promptly toned down the flirting.  We thought about buying a wheelchair, but when they told us it wasn&#039;t for sale, we decided against it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&#039;s when &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; got some balls.  They were made of brass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We went out to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt;&#039;s car.  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; wrote his phone number on the back of a savings deposit slip.  He went back inside the store for a few minutes.  I used the time to look at the pamphlet that came with my new pocket knife explaining all of the features my knife doesn&#039;t have.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; told me later that the girl said, &quot;were you talking about the Big Lebowski earlier?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;I forgot to mention that we were talking about the &lt;/i&gt;Big Lebowski&lt;i&gt; earlier.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;yeah, we&#039;re having a Big Lebowski party tomorrow night if you wanted to come . . .&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Allow me to bold the words which paticularly stabbed &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; in the heart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;I don&#039;t know.  I&#039;m working here all weekend and it&#039;s my &lt;b&gt;one year anniversary&lt;/b&gt; with my &lt;b&gt;boyfriend&lt;/b&gt;.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At least he tried.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We set out to explore the Goodwill store on the other-other side of town.  We were talking about the girl we met at the first Goodwill store so much that we almost forgot about the organ.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Did you forget about the organ?&quot; I asked.  If &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; could have done a screeching U-turn right then and there, he would have.  He may have failed at getting a girl, but he would succeed at getting an organ.  Off we sped to the gypsy lady&#039;s house.  &lt;i&gt;Act of fate B:  If I hadn&#039;t remembered about it, we would never have gotten it.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We inspected the device, just to make sure it was something we really wanted.  The problem is that this was never a thing we really wanted.  We overcame that problem and went inside to inquire.  Inquire we did.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The gypsy lady was sitting in a chair, apparently somewhat crippled, with various medical supplies scattered around her.  She had a cast on her leg.  I wonder if she saw that injury coming.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The asking price is fourty dollars.&quot;  We had a hard time hearing her, because she had a few obnoxious dogs that kept barking.  &quot;Everything works perfectly.&quot;  Usually when people say &quot;everything works perfectly&quot; something probably doesn&#039;t work perfectly.  That was something I learned on this adventure.  We couldn&#039;t get it immediately, because &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; didn&#039;t have fourty dollars cash, and his car was full of coffin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, I had to go, so I wasn&#039;t with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/gordonjingers&quot; class=&quot;black&quot;&gt;Andrew&lt;/a&gt; when he made the purchase.  Simmilarly, I have to go now, so I&#039;ll continue the story in a little bit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/content/news.php?post=00153&quot;&gt;Read part 2 of &lt;i&gt;The Curse of the Gypsy&#039;s Organ&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

