data.text:
&lt;p&gt;Soda comes in many shapes and sizes, but which one is right for you?  I can&#039;t really answer that, because it&#039;s all pretty bad for you.  However, we can do a cost-benefit analisys of each type of soda container, and decide which is the most bang for your buck.  All prices I have listed here were taken from the Speedway convenience store just next door to my apartment building.  Can you find better prices?  I would prefer to have average prices on this chart, so if you go somewhere that sells soda, please take note of how much all of these items cost and post the data here (along with where you found them).  As I add more data to the chart, it will approach &quot;true average.&quot;  When the prices listed here are close to &quot;true average,&quot; you can see if prices you get are above or below average.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table style=&quot;margin-left: 10%&quot;&gt;
&lt;tr style=&quot;font-weight: bold&quot;&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;width: 280px;&quot;&gt;Container Size&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;width: 200px;&quot;&gt;Number &#039;o&#039; Ounces&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td style=&quot;width: 100px;&quot;&gt;Unit Price&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Price per OZ&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Single Can&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;12 OZ&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;$.79&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;$.065833&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;12 Can box (fridge pack)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;144&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;4.29&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.02979167&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Two 12 can boxes (special deal)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;288&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;5.98&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.02076389&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;One Liter(re) Bottle&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;33.8140226&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.29&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.03814985&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Two Liter(re) Bottle&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;67.6280452&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.59&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.023511&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Single Serving Bottle (2.5 servings)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1.39&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.0695&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Two single bottles (5 servings)&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;40&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;2.00&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;.05&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These results are partially fascinating.  It looks like going with the special 12-pack deal is the cheapest (per ounce) way to go when you buy soda.  The interesting thing is that it is also the most expensive (per unit) way to go.    It is important to note that this chart does not include the loss of value when one of your friends/acquaintances steals some of the cans from your pack.  The Speedway did not have any 24-pack boxes.  Is a 24-pack a better value?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think cans taste better than bottles, and that they hold their temperature better.  Do you think the type of container changes the value of the drink held within?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have been buying a lot of 20-ounce bottles lately.  I have been saving up the codes printed on the inside of the bottle caps.  It is disheartening to know that bottles are the worst value when purchasing soda.  I am 38 points, or 10 bottles, away from my goal.  Does getting free crap with the packaging increase the value of the drink held within?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A single serving of soda is about 8 ounces (one cup).  None of the containers on this list are separated into 8 ounce servings.  Why do single-use cans contain 1.5 servings?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By far the best deal (not included on this list) is the &lt;b&gt;fountain drink&lt;/b&gt;.  Most gas stations and convenience stores sell fountain drinks nowadays.  You can buy 32 ounces of soda (including ice) for as little as $.65.  That is a value of as little as &lt;b&gt;2 cents per ounce&lt;/b&gt;.  You can approach the value of two 12-packs with the convenience of not having anyone steal your soda.  If you fill your cup with ice, how much soda are you actually getting?  Do gas stations expect you to fill half your fountain drinks with ice?  This would make an excellent &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cockeyed.com/inside/howmuchinside.html&quot;&gt;&quot;How much is inside&quot; adventure&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The worst deal, it would appear, is the &quot;Single Serving&quot; bottle.  The 20 ounce bottle has been around for a very long time.  Is the added plastic flavor worth the extra 4 cents per ounce?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does anyone even buy 1-liter bottles?&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following is a list of the top 10 things I want to see in &lt;i&gt;Die Hard 4&lt;/i&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;Yipee Kay Yay&quot;&lt;/b&gt; John McClain needs to say it at some point before the very end of the film.  He says it in the trailer, so I know it is in there.  I just hope they didn&#039;t throw it in at the end.  Speaking of endings, &lt;i&gt;Die Hard 4&lt;/i&gt; needs&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;a better ending than &lt;i&gt;Die Hard with a Vengance&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;  Ten extra minutes of gratuitous and uninteresting action, completely out of place and tedious, just upsets me as a sort-of writer.  I&#039;ll tell you what does have to be in it at the end, though.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;John McClain has to fight a big German dude, who he ends up defeating using chains somehow.  Lookout, though, because the German dude isn&#039;t actually dead.&lt;/b&gt;  Also,&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;McClain shows his technophobia.&lt;/b&gt;  They&#039;ve established that John dislikes new technology, and that was just talking about phones on planes.  I want to see him really pissed off about all these damn cell phones.  The movie seems to be based on computer hackers.  There&#039;s a lot of good writing potential there that I hope they don&#039;t let go to waste.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bonnie Bodelia as Holly Gennero.&lt;/b&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000889/&quot;&gt;IMDB&lt;/a&gt; has already crushed this hope.  It would be nice to actually see Mrs. John McClain again.  Speaking of reprising characters,&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Reginald VelJohnson and Samuel L. Jackson both need to reprise their roles&lt;/b&gt; somehow, preferably in the same scene and over the phone.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The enemy better be a group of German mercenary terrorists who all use MP5&#039;s for some reason.&lt;/b&gt;  I wouldn&#039;t mind a Steyer Aug showing up at some point, though.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;John McClain wears a white tank top&lt;/b&gt;, which becomes a shade of dark green-gray and splattered with various people&#039;s blood by the end of the movie.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Numerous Christmas references&lt;/b&gt;, despite the fact that the film is set in mid July.  Along those same lines, I&#039;d like to hear&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;Winter Wonderland&quot;&lt;/b&gt; playing during the credits.  Let&#039;s get back to what makes &lt;i&gt;Die Hard&lt;/i&gt; great, shall we?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I would be nice to have a really awesome action movie like the good old days, but I just don&#039;t see it happening.  &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Die Hard 4&lt;/i&gt; is rated PG-13.&lt;/b&gt;  That is really disheartening and depressing.  You can make your own assumptions, but I doubt we&#039;re going to see someone get chopped in half again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have fun at the movies this weekend, and stay tuned for my list of the top 10 things I hope to see in &lt;i&gt;Transformers&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

