data.text:
&lt;p&gt;My friend Andrew &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through&quot;&gt;Preston&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;Monkey&lt;/b&gt; recently brought &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/tang.php&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; to my attention.  It seems that perhaps I was wrong about Tang disappearing.  This is a curious development.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The quantity goes up to 30.  That would be $135, and it would make 180 Quarts or 45 Gallons or one third of a butt of Tang.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How can I raise $135 for the sake of hording Tang?  Perhaps I could get some sort of government grant.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ll start with a quick update before I get to the nitty gritty, because shoe it&#039;s been a while.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason I haven&#039;t made any updates recently is because I&#039;ve been very busy with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building a &quot;Coy Pond&quot; for my aunt, and hanging out with Marcie.  If you&#039;re either myself or my cousin Pat, you&#039;ll think that&#039;s hilarious.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Starting school.  Nobody thinks that&#039;s hilarious at all.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working on my new job, at which I&#039;m typing this right now.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working on the new Crazy Monkeys website, which you can sneak a gander at &lt;a href=&quot;http://web.ics.purdue.edu/~smcgill/monkeys&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, until I finish it and it goes up at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thecrazymonkeys.com&quot;&gt;The Crazy Monkeys&lt;/a&gt; website.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But since you don&#039;t care about me or my life (why should you, you&#039;ve got your own life to not care about), none of that is important.  What is important, though is an idea for a social experiment, which everyone can help with.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

