data.text:
&lt;p&gt;John and I just got our rebate checks from Corsair for that sweet RAM I bought over the summer, six to eight weeks ago.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Check out how awesome they are.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/rebate/envelopes.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/rebate/john.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/rebate/shauron.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; . . . wait a minute . . . &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m in the Entrepreneurship class, and I have to write a paper about the project we had for our mid-term. It was a group project, and we had to find an Entrepreneur and interview him about his business, videotape it, and edit the video into a seven minute showcase video.&lt;/p&gt;

So we had to go to the Indianapolis Airport and talk to this guy who fixes up corporate jets. It turned out well, so whatever. Here&#039;s the description of the paper I have to write (which is due tomorrow). This is directly copied from the assignment description.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;em&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each of you will write a paper on your personal impressions and what you learned from the interview itself and the entire process of completing it.  This is not to be a recap or summary of the interview.  It is a write up of what you learned from the whole process.  Questions to help give you direction:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What went well?&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;What did not go so well?&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;What would you do differently the next time you have a complex group project such as this?&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;What did you take away from the comments and experiences of the entrepreneur?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Someone always asks: &quot;How long should this paper be?&quot;  The real answer is simply, long enough to thoroughly cover the topics.  As guidance I will add this -an amazingly good writer could not capture all of this in less than three full pages.  On the other hand, a reasonably good writer, one who edits well, who is concise yet comprehensive, can do a very good job in six or seven pages.  It is due on October 21 at the beginning of class (turn in a printed copy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/em&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.viddler.com/explore/Shauvon/videos/1/&quot;&gt;Here&#039;s the video, in case you care.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Okay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my life, I&#039;ve asked why Humans are here. What is the meaning of life? I have come to the conclusion that we are here to produce the ultimate work of art. Human civilization has led to one ultimate point, the single event that justifies our entire existence. That event has happened. I know exactly what it was.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ed_Banger_Records&quot;&gt;Ed Banger Records&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dear Andrew,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How are you? I am fine. You&#039;ve been in Europe for about a month now. I know you know that, I&#039;m just recapping what the situation is so you know I have reserved brain space for remembering what happens to you. Anyway, you&#039;ve been in Europe for like a month or whatever. Or maybe you were in England for some of that, I don&#039;t know. I hope you&#039;re having fun. I hope you&#039;re having tons of stupid fun with your big, stupid face.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I decided to write you this letter to show you how much awesome fun we&#039;re all having here now that you&#039;ve finally put an entire ocean between you and us. Yeah, we&#039;re having tons of funs all over the place like a billion, and most of it is in regards to you getting the H out. We&#039;re always like, &quot;here&#039;s a toast to that guy Andrew and his no longer being here!&quot; Then everybody gets really quiet for a few minutes, and I try to think about dinosaurs because that&#039;s what I used to do when I was a kid and I was trying not to cry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ol&#039; number 3 is still doing well. That weird secondary light in the bathroom has gone out, and we can&#039;t figure out how to take it apart to replace it. We&#039;re going to tell Jonny Bash about it and have him send that skinny dude to fix it, but they&#039;re really busy right now with leasing season. Also, Bash&#039;m just got elected to the County Council, so I kinda don&#039;t want to approach him until that blows over a little bit, because I&#039;m sure he&#039;s got a lot to say about the whole situation. John renewed his lease for next year, which means we don&#039;t have to worry about cleaning up all those labels and marker on the walls and stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I finally bought peanut butter the other day. After over a year since I moved out of my old apartment, I&#039;m out of the stockpile I collected as part of the Meisner Collection. That leaves the footrests and that coffee table thing in my room as the only remaining items that I stole from Dan (well, except for the frying pan, the Foreman grill, that jacket that doesn&#039;t fit me, and that one spoon).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oh, Harland Fankboner has a new Fresh Idea card. That&#039;s new. Remember that time we went to the store and I bought a whole box of Sweet Tarts Ropes? I haven&#039;t eaten any Sweet Tarts Ropes in like three months. Isn&#039;t that about when you left town? Just look how much healthier I am now that I don&#039;t have your big ol&#039; stanky ass holding me down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Monkeys are going to do a show at IU again this year. I&#039;m really excited for it, even though the email invitation we got and all the documents are made out to Tim Franklin. We&#039;ve got a show with the Ship of Fools on November 22, too. It&#039;s another charity show, this time just for Habitat for Humanity. Joe has been in contact with the charity, and I told him to tell them that if they don&#039;t send some of their people to the show this year, then I&#039;ll just keep all the money for myself. I have to redo the combined logo for the flier for this show, since the Crazy Monkeys have a new logo. We still haven&#039;t cashed that check yet (you know the one I mean). Sorry about that. We&#039;ve had a lot of other stuff to think about, and we&#039;re also pretty lazy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&#039;t think Joe actually told the Habitat people that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just so you know, I got a catalog today from &lt;em&gt;Things Remembered&lt;/em&gt;, that place that engraves people&#039;s names into metal junk. So you and your little friend Andy Briston have gotten me onto somebody&#039;s mailing list. I hope you&#039;re both happy. I&#039;ll probably get these catalogs for the rest of my lonely, sweet-tarts-rope-free life. Just so you know, I could totally snatch a sterling silver heart dangle for $65 with like four whole words engraved on it. I&#039;m going to buy one that says &quot;Andy Briston died this year.&quot; There&#039;s only a few more weeks in 2008, you know.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bottlecap bucket is pretty much level to the rim, so it&#039;s time to either do something with these or find a larger bucket. I bet we could have found one at Goodwill, but John never wants to go there. Remember that time we got cursed by a gypsy and then you fled the continent, sticking me with it? That gypsy has moved across town into a way nicer house in a way nicer neighborhood (or at least her &quot;ESP Readings&quot; sign has). She&#039;s doing way better now that she&#039;s gotten rid of the curse. Maybe in Europe you can find some sort of ancient temple that does curse clensings and you can have them do something about it. Maybe you could dig up a cardinal&#039;s bones and perform some sort of ritual or something. You should dig up a cardinal&#039;s bones anyway. It couldn&#039;t hurt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I made a video for my sister a couple weeks ago. You remember when you used to sit on the couch playing Half Life while I was working on projects and stuff? John just sits in his room playing Half Life. It&#039;s not the same. Anyway, I put the video online so you (or any joker who&#039;s reading my totally private letter to you) can see it. It&#039;s pretty hilarious, plus it has Justice in it. If it ever finishes rendering, I&#039;ll put a link up on this website or something.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, that&#039;s about all I have tonight. Good ol&#039; Friday night. . . Remember when I would be like, &quot;hey, it&#039;s Friday, let&#039;s go to a bar!&quot; and then you would give me that look like you think I&#039;m a moron, and I would totally play it off like I was kidding and laugh awkwardly for too long, then we&#039;d go back to playing Team Fortress 2? John actually listens to me all the time, and we keep getting stuck at a bar because I didn&#039;t realize that I was just kidding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That new Zombie Team Fortress game is almost out, and I played the demo. It&#039;s pretty sweet, but I probably won&#039;t get it since I don&#039;t have any friends here anymore who&#039;ll play it with me. John just sits at his computer looking up wikipedia stuff in Linux drinking Cosmopolitans.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ok. Have tons of funs on Europe. Party till you puke and all that. Let me know when you do that thing I asked you to do (not digging up a cardinal; the other thing).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sincerely,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shauvon&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Deny Conformity Entertainment Network now has another facet to its glorious empire.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A couple friends of mine are writing a web comic, and I set up a little webpage for them to host it on. The strip is called &lt;i&gt;Circle, Square, Triangle&lt;/i&gt; and it can be viewed at &lt;a href=&quot;http://cst.denyconformity.com&quot;&gt;http://cst.denyconformity.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So my sister, Aili, attended some sort of conference thing. She needed to prepare an eight minute introduction for herself. Obviously, that meant that &lt;i&gt;I&lt;/i&gt; had to prepare an eight minute introduction, in the form of a super-sweet video. That video is done, and you can view it here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;object classid=&quot;clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000&quot; codebase=&quot;http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=8,0,0,0&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; height=&quot;480&quot; id=&quot;FLVPlayer&quot;&gt;
  &lt;param name=&quot;movie&quot; value=&quot;/assets/aili/FLVPlayer_Progressive.swf&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;param name=&quot;salign&quot; value=&quot;lt&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;param name=&quot;quality&quot; value=&quot;high&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;param name=&quot;scale&quot; value=&quot;noscale&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;param name=&quot;FlashVars&quot; value=&quot;&amp;MM_ComponentVersion=1&amp;skinName=/assets/aili/Clear_Skin_3&amp;streamName=/assets/aili/aili&amp;autoPlay=true&amp;autoRewind=true&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;embed src=&quot;/assets/aili/FLVPlayer_Progressive.swf&quot; flashvars=&quot;&amp;MM_ComponentVersion=1&amp;skinName=/assets/aili/Clear_Skin_3&amp;streamName=/assets/aili/aili&amp;autoPlay=true&amp;autoRewind=true&quot; quality=&quot;high&quot; scale=&quot;noscale&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; height=&quot;480&quot; name=&quot;FLVPlayer&quot; salign=&quot;LT&quot; type=&quot;application/x-shockwave-flash&quot; pluginspage=&quot;http://www.adobe.com/shockwave/download/download.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So that last thing might make you glad you aren&#039;t me, but we both know that isn&#039;t the case. You still wish you were me. Let me give you ten reasons why.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two Classes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
One of which is a 200 level course. I don&#039;t think I really have to explain this one.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Height&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Face it. You wish you were six eight.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free shit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
I won&#039;t tell you what or how, just in case somebody wants to arrest me (probably from jealousy), but I &lt;b&gt;C&lt;/b&gt;an get a lot of really expen&lt;b&gt;S&lt;/b&gt;ive things &lt;b&gt;4&lt;/b&gt; free.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Web development is like play&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
I really enjoy putting an application together, which is why I do it on average for 6 hours a day. Since I consider it more like playing a video game than doing work, I really only do like 2 hours of work a day, and most of that is going to or from class. Oh, also I get paid to do it.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No obligations to man or machine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
I have a part time job, a few modest bills every month, and two pretty easy classes (see #1). Those are the only minor obligations I have. I ask myself &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; I should get out of bed every morning because I don&#039;t &lt;em&gt;have&lt;/em&gt; to get out of bed. I ask &quot;why am I here?&quot; because I don&#039;t have to be here.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Detachment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
I feel alienated and isolated from everyone around me, but I prefer it this way. It really sucks sometimes, sure, but you have no idea how freeing it is to be completely detached from everyone around you. I don&#039;t have to follow anybody&#039;s rules (except the government, with the exception of #3).&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The soundtrack rocks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Listen to what I listen to almost constantly, as loudly as I listen to it, and you&#039;ll be ready to punch cars out of your way and smash down walls.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthy and chemically pure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Except for the lung thing (which is really only enough of a problem to be a conversation piece), and the obvious psychological hurdles, I&#039;ve never had a serious health problem. Also, barely any drugs ever enter my system, and the ones that do aren&#039;t any more powerful than anti-histamines.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tim, John, Mike, Tom, Logan, Joe, Eli, Kelsey, Lauren, Matt&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
I know, you have cool friends, too. Well fuck you and your friends. Mine are better. I sincerely believe that. Last Friday evening, a room full of people all decided that they would rather watch me and my friends than you and yours (unless you&#039;re one of those people I listed, in which case you are one of my friends (and yes, I realize that there were other shows and things going on that night that had audiences, but whatever)). I get to watch the Crazy Monkeys perform pretty much every day.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My computer(s)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Sure, my desktop crashes occasionally, but it&#039;s a quad core machine with 8 gigabytes of ram and DirectX 10.1 capability and a TERRORbyte of hard drive space. Plus it has Vista on it, which is better than anything you might be using. Also, my Eee is better than your laptop.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There you go, the top ten reasons you wish you were me. I&#039;m just saying this to make sure that we&#039;re clear. I might have trouble motivating myself and understanding what my place is, but there is nobody I would rather be.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess I should also mention that I was inspired to do this by one of those disgusting Facebook chain letter things.&lt;/p&gt;

