data.text:
&lt;p&gt;I went to Chicago all weekend, and the town convinced me that I want to move there. So now I&#039;m really excited to start applying for some real jobs up in Chicago. I&#039;ve finished my resume, so if anybody is looking for a C#, Javascript, PHP or ASP developer, give it a look. I&#039;ll be graduating this May with a big, giant BS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/portfolio/shauvon_mcgill_resume.pdf&quot;&gt;Shauvon McGill&#039;s Resum&Atilde;&copy; (PDF)&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;a href=&quot;http://vevmo.com/f56/shauvons-incredible-shrinking-tops-1306/&quot; target=&quot;torres&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; is creepy as hell.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hey, Shauvon Torres, I know you&#039;re just working with what you&#039;ve got, but maybe you should just give it up and find a &lt;em&gt;real job&lt;/em&gt;. I realize life is pretty tough for us Shauvons, but you really need to take it easy with the whole &quot;super slut&quot; thing. I know what you&#039;re going to say, though. You&#039;re going to say that you have absolutely no other marketable skills, and since you&#039;ve put so much investment capital down on those . . . assets, it would be a waste to quit now. Well, I hate to break it to you, but all the assets in the world aren&#039;t going to make up for being partially retarded and having a tiny head. Oh, I&#039;m sorry, I wasn&#039;t going to bring up the tiny head thing, but it slipped out. Seriously, it&#039;s smaller than your too-expensive boobs. Ok, I&#039;m sorry, that was a low blow. It&#039;s just that I&#039;m a little upset that you&#039;re doing &lt;em&gt;that&lt;/em&gt; with my name. &lt;em&gt;My name.&lt;/em&gt; Please stop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fine. Here&#039;s what I say. I wanted some sort of sign that I should man-up and make this stupid TV sitcom and whatever. This is my sign. I will do whatever I can to make sure that I am the most famous Shauvon on the planet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So help me, God.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Step one of Operation &quot;Outdo Shauvon Torres&quot; is finishing my pilot (which is actually two pilots, for two opposing shows). I&#039;m well on my way, and I hope to be done with it by tonight or tomorrow. Does anybody want to read it and tell me how awesome it is / I am?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In case anybody was wondering, here&#039;s a quick description of the show: &lt;em&gt;A college junior just finished a major project, and now he finds himself lonely, bored, and questioning his place in the world. Meanwhile, a theatre student begins to wonder if her long-time boyfriend is really &quot;the one.&quot; These two people have never met, and their lives seem to have nothing in common. However, the consonance and dissonance of the universe brings them together in ways you&#039;ll never expect. Worlds collide and lives will never be the same in this new comedy series from the creators of &lt;/em&gt;Denyconformity.com&lt;em&gt;! &lt;/em&gt;Consonance&lt;em&gt; brings us together, and &lt;/em&gt;Dissonance&lt;em&gt; tears us apart, but which will prevail . . . ?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get all titillated just thinking about it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. In the world of Big Beat Electronic duos, The Chemical Brothers are Radiohead, the Crystal Method is Coldplay, and the Prodigy is Oasis. I thought that up the other day when I heard that the Prodigy has a new album coming out. I&#039;m pretty excited about it.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What if you had a day with no consequences? You&#039;re going to die the next day, so you have 24 hours to do whatever you want. What would you do? Who would you talk to?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What would you listen to if you knew it would be the last song you ever heard?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What would you say to someone if you &lt;em&gt;knew&lt;/em&gt; it was your last conversation?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What would you eat? What would you touch? What laws would you break?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Really think about it. Don&#039;t just think about thinking about it, just to humor me. I&#039;m just text on a screen, so you don&#039;t have to make me feel better. I&#039;m doing this for you. It&#039;s important that you think of something now, before I corrupt your brain with the point I&#039;m trying to make. Did you think of something? Good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, what if you weren&#039;t dying tomorrow (hopefully this is actually the case). Which of those things would you still do? Any of them? &lt;em&gt;Why wouldn&#039;t you do a thing you specifically want to do before you die just because you don&#039;t know you are yet?&lt;/em&gt; Is consequence worse than death?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do one of those things, anyway. &lt;em&gt;Right now.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

