data.text:
&lt;p&gt;It occured to me, just now, that I never really appreciate any of the moments that I &lt;em&gt;don&#039;t&lt;/em&gt; have the hiccups. I only pay attention to the times when I have them. I haven&#039;t had them in a while (this is probably going to jinx me), I just thought about that for some reason.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My eyebrow has stopped twitching, for now.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So here&#039;s a thing about me. My life is ending on May 9th, 2009.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&#039;s when my last class happens, a final for Physics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On may 11th (the 10th is a Sunday), I begin the &quot;rest of my life.&quot; Working every single day, all day, until I die. I might take a break on my birthday.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After May 9th, 2009, everything I know will change. Well, okay, so my lease will continue through August, and my job will remain indefinitely, but the point is that my life as I know it will be done. Yes, I will miss it, but judging from how generally unhappy I am most of the time, I shouldn&#039;t mourn for long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speaking of which, I&#039;ve been especially unhappy lately. It&#039;s (that&#039;s &quot;it was&quot;) my last Spring Break ever, and I failed my goal of seeing at least one boob. My pilot hit a wall (in my head), and I completely lost interest in producing it. I&#039;ve lost touch with reason. I feel like I have no point. I can&#039;t say anything that hasn&#039;t already been said. I can&#039;t do anything that hasn&#039;t already been done. Plus, you know, my life is going to end in a couple months.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My problem is that I can&#039;t think of a single thing that I really want to do. There are things I&#039;m mildly interested in, a lot of stuff I like to do to kill time, but nothing I would want to do every day from now until the end of time. That&#039;s been really bumming me out. Especially since five months from now I&#039;ll be homeless, and jobless, on top of being directionless and careless. That&#039;s terrifying on top of depressing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I feel better now, though. I feel better because I&#039;ve pushed the &quot;end of life as I know it&quot; back a bit. I found something that I want to do. Instead of fear the &quot;end of my life&quot; I&#039;m going to bring it on. I&#039;m going to just let it all go. I&#039;m going to say goodbye to my life, and I&#039;m going to leave. I will walk straight into the abyss, and I won&#039;t be coming back. I mean, this &lt;em&gt;me&lt;/em&gt; won&#039;t be coming back.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve never done anything particularly hard. I&#039;ve never done anything particularly interesting, frankly. Before I get a real job and spend the rest of my life building websites or whatever else I&#039;ll be stuck doing, I&#039;m going to have one real adventure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m going to Burning Man.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

