&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;I&#039;m waiting. What happened yesterday? Do you want to talk about it? YOU TALK ME NOW&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/6.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt; . . . what?&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/7.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;First off, the friends system hasn&#039;t changed at all, only the home page has been changed. For that matter, photos haven&#039;t changed at all, either, except that they now have rounded corners. Ok, so the higher emphasis on &quot;fan&quot; pages probably just signifies Facebook&#039;s true desire to serve as the world&#039;s greatest advertising platform, but I&#039;m sure that&#039;s what you were getting at. As for why your friends are gone, well maybe it&#039;s because you&#039;re a barely coherent moron.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/8.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Maybe you should sit down for a moment and take a deep breath. You should probably see a doctor about that internet-triggered vertigo.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/9.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;The thing I find interesting about these posts is that they would have all had to be typed at exactly the same moment. Also, all five of these people (well, four people and one shoe) thought that just voting &quot;I do not like the layout&quot; just didn&#039;t quite say &quot;I do not like the layout&quot; enough for them. Essentially 85% of the comments were something to the effect of &quot;I do not like the layout.&quot; Thanks, that&#039;s really helpful, shoe.&lt;/div&gt;

