&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/18.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;This is actually a long-used web design term.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/19.jpg&quot; /&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;This one isn&#039;t really that bad, I just needed to include it to make sense of the next one. Ok, so Lukas doesn&#039;t know the difference between &quot;you&#039;re&quot; and &quot;your&quot; but at least he&#039;s not a complete moron. Like this guy:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/fb/21.jpg&quot; /&gt;

