&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Here&#039;s to you, Rebel. We&#039;ve been through a lot, and it&#039;s with a heavy heart that I say goodbye. (by the way, this is the first picture on DenyConformity.com taken by my new camera)&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or &lt;strong&gt;Shauvon Should Not be Allowed to Have Money (part 1)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I have a new camera. This shouldn&#039;t be news to you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s a Canon 50D, with a Tamron 18 - 270 mm lens. I have a 4 gigabyte Compact Flash card, and a Canon 430EX speedlight (but the speedlight isn&#039;t new). It&#039;s probably the most awesome thing I&#039;ve ever owned (except maybe that limited-edition signed copy of &lt;em&gt;Ara&lt;/em&gt; that I have around here somewhere). The new camera, which I call &lt;em&gt;Carus&lt;/em&gt; (a Latin word for &quot;expensive&quot;), has 15 megapixels. It shoots Canon Raw files that are around 25 megabytes a file. My old camera, a Canon 350D (apparently lower numbers mean better cameras), had 8 megapixels and created files that were about 7 megabytes each. I can take just over 200 pictures on a 2 gigabyte CF card with my old camera. With &lt;em&gt;Carus&lt;/em&gt;, using a 4 gig card, I can take about 150 pictures. That&#039;s how much bigger 15 megapixels are.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pictures my old camera took were plenty big. With 8 megapixels, you can easily print poster-sized versions of photographs, create desktop backgrounds that span two widescreen monitors, and quickly fill hard drives with pictures. Carus &lt;em&gt;takes photographs with almost twice the resolution and over three times the size of my old camera. &lt;strong&gt;I can substantially crop photographs taken by &lt;/em&gt;Carus&lt;em&gt;, and they will still be larger than anything my old camera took.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; That gives me a great deal of power as a photographer. A 15 megapixel file is 4752 pixels wide by 3168 pixels tall.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can see just how big that is by looking at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.denyconformity.com/assets/images/50D-1/15_megapixels.jpg&quot; target=&quot;15megapixels&quot;&gt;this 6.51 megabyte JPEG file&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Carus is &lt;em&gt;Heavy&lt;/em&gt; (its full name is &quot;Gravis, Ergo Carus&quot; or &quot;Heavy, therefore Expensive&quot;). When I hold my old camera, it feels like a child&#039;s toy compared to this beast. Aside from making me feel like a real man, Carus&#039;s weight makes it a little difficult to carry around all the time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ve taken a lot of pictures with Carus. You don&#039;t really have to try hard to get pictures substantially better than pictures you would take with a &quot;sans-carus&quot; camera.&lt;/p&gt;
