&lt;p&gt;These photographs are a sign of things to come. 2009 will be a good year for DenyConformity.com.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of my best friends, Tim, and another one of my best friends, Mary, had their wedding on Saturday. I will always remember it as one of the high points of my life.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is not often that one gets the opportunity to witness perfection. On Saturday, I did. I could not be happier for the couple, and I feel so honored that they allowed me to share just a tiny piece of their perfection. Tim absolutely adores Mary, and Mary absolutely adores Tim. Their relationship is one of the most beautiful things I will ever see; of that I am certain. To wish them happiness feels futile. It is obvious that they will know nothing but happiness. They will know nothing but perfection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images//small_tim_mary.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 400px; margin: auto; display: block&quot; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Here&#039;s to perfection.&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Terrified.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Terrified.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&#039;s the primary component of my mood the last week (and day). You see, I&#039;ve moved to Chicago. I&#039;ve moved to Chicago, I&#039;m in way over my head, I&#039;m alone, I&#039;m out of my element, and I&#039;m &lt;em&gt;terrified&lt;/em&gt;. I&#039;ve done this thing, this &quot;grand adventure&quot; that is becoming an adult. I don&#039;t want to do it, and I don&#039;t know why I did. There are 2.8 million people here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;2.8 Million people.&lt;/em&gt; (I Googled &quot;2.8 million&quot; to see just how much that is, and interestingly that&#039;s the number of homes that weren&#039;t ready for the DTV switch. I bet those people don&#039;t have TV anymore and they&#039;re &lt;em&gt;terrified&lt;/em&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What am I doing? What am I doing? What am I doing? I feel so out of place. I&#039;m a 20 minute train ride from Downtown Chicago. I can ride my bike to the &lt;em title=&quot;Willis Tower&quot;&gt;Sears Tower&lt;/em&gt;. I saw these comedy people tonight, these girls who do improv (friends of my roommate). They&#039;re funny, sophisticated, and interesting, and I&#039;m just some fucking hayseed from the middle of nowhere. I don&#039;t know how to behave. I don&#039;t know where to go. I don&#039;t even know what I&#039;m terrified of.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You know sometimes when you fart and for a split second you think you might have done more than just fart? That&#039;s how I feel, except it&#039;s &lt;em&gt;all the time&lt;/em&gt;. I&#039;m constantly did-I-just-poop-my-pants terrified. It&#039;s not going anywhere, and neither are the 2.8 million people living right outside my bedroom.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;God damn it, what am I going to do?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe what terrifies me so much is the fact that I&#039;m actually doing alright here.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

