data.text:
&lt;p&gt;Dear friends and family of DenyConformity.com,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found out today that the company I work for, Tiger Team Solutions, is being shut down. The state of &lt;a href=&quot;http://smac.denyconformity.com/economy.php&quot;&gt;the Economy&lt;/a&gt; has finally made its way into the digital realm, and there simply aren&#039;t enough clients around to sustain a company, even one with as little overhead as Tiger Team. I feel deeply, truly sorry for my boss, John Powers, because I&#039;m sure this is an extremely stressful and difficult situation for him. I hope that your thoughts, and your prayers (if you are so inclined) will go out to him and his wife in the coming months.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This also, as you have probably assumed, puts me out of a job. I am trying to see this as an opportunity, not a curse. I will have some time to finish my latest project, a screenplay about a new college graduate who is looking for a job in Chicago (it&#039;s a creative stretch, I know). I am hoping that I can find a new job in the next two weeks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have often wondered what I would do if I lost my job. I think it&#039;s an interesting thing to think about sometimes, like what you would do if you were mugged, or how you would survive a zombie invasion, or what you would say if you were the guest on an episode of &lt;em&gt;Top Gear&lt;/em&gt;. I know how much money I need to have each month to survive, so I can estimate how long I can last without an income before I am completely &quot;brokd.&quot; I feel I can last a little while under my current situation (although my current situation is not without turmoil, which I will be sure to explain when it all blows over). This will, at the very least, help me understand what it is to be an adult.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How long could you last if you lost your job? How much money would you have to save to extend that? These are questions you might want to consider, in case you end up in a situation similar to mine. I will be sure to keep you all updated on my progress, and let you know what the job scene is like in the big &quot;shy-town.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the mean time, if anybody out there knows of any freelance web design, photography, music production, graphic design, programming, videography, video post-production, or writing jobs out there, let me know. I&#039;ve got some time on my hands.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And if you see me, remind me that life is actually worth it some times.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks, everybody, for your support (that I&#039;m assuming you&#039;re going to give me).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-Shauvon McGill&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;When Marco Polo came at last to Cathay, seven hundred years ago, did he not feel - and did his heart not falter as he realized - that this great and splendid capital of an empire had had its being all the years of his life and far longer, and that he had been ignorant of it? That it was in need of nothing from him, from Venice, from Europe? That it was full of wonders beyond his understanding? That his arrival was a matter of no importance whatever? We know that he felt these things, and so has any a traveler in foreign parts who did not know what he was going to find. There is nothing that cuts you down to size like coming to some strange and marvelous place where no one even stops to notice that you stare about you.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-&lt;em&gt;Watership Down&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

