&lt;p&gt;I have been finding myself complaining about the world more and more lately. War. Famine. Oil spills. Everything is a mess. I&#039;ve decided to take it upon myself, as a person on the internet, to send my complaints to the person I think could to the most to fix it, the President of Earth. I don&#039;t know why nobody has thought of that before. There&#039;s no need to thank me, the benefit of having a better world is reward enough.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, I guess if you want to send me gifts and stuff, you can.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Read the entire letter&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear President of Earth,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How are you? I am just fine. I hope everything is going well for you there in your high chambers or whatever you call it. I&#039;m sure you&#039;ve heard enough of this, but I would still like to congratulate you on your appointment to the highest position of respect and power in what is probably the greatest planet the Human Race has ever known (except, you know, wherever the pyramids came from). I&#039;m sure it&#039;s no small order to take the mantle of Leader of the Entire World, and you have a great deal of things to take care of. However, it&#039;s certainly a great achievement, and I hope you take a moment to step back and acknowledge what a thing you&#039;ve done there. I don&#039;t think I could get myself elected (or crowned, I&#039;m not sure how that works) President of an entire planet, even if I really tried hard for a few months. If your parents aren&#039;t proud of you by now, they probably never will be so you can stop trying to win their attention. I mean, just being able to introduce yourself as &quot;President of Earth&quot; has to make up for all the hard work and stress you have to deal with. You probably live in Babeland, USA. Actually, you probably live in Dubai, because that&#039;s totally where I would go if I were president of Earth. Wherever you are, I&#039;m sure you&#039;re knee deep in all the hot chicks you can stand (or stand on, which I would probably do if I were President of Earth).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would love to do nothing but admire Your great, all-encompassing power and grace, Your Majesty (do I call You that?), but I do have some important issues to bring to Your attention instead. I realize that you probably have millions of things to think about at any given moment (many of them in Spanish, even), but I really think that the following issues are critical to the continued success of Human Beings as a unified species, and they are therefor of utmost importance to you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My first, and arguably most important complaint has to do with the fact that you don&#039;t exist. I&#039;m sure you can see what a hindrance this is to your ability to lead Earth into a time of continued prosperity. I can&#039;t tell you what a disappointment it is every time I wake up and realize that even though everybody in the world can talk to one another and pretty much everybody lives together in one society, we don&#039;t actually have any kind of unifying government to do anything to make the world a better place for everybody (and we all know the U.N. doesn&#039;t really count). I am tempted to include the word &quot;yet&quot; when saying you don&#039;t exist, but, sadly, I am not sure if you will ever exist at all. Call me cynical, but considering how blas&amp;#233; and, quite frankly, incompetent your administration has been so far, I would not be surprised if they continue to not exist for the foreseeable future. I think I speak for pretty much everybody when I say that this isn&#039;t really that great. I would ask, therefore, that you address this issue as soon as you possibly can. With power as seemingly limitless and mighty as yours, I&#039;m sure one could easily pull the necessary strings and jump through all of the proper &quot;hoops&quot; to create oneself. I look forward to your first speech when you explain exactly how you pulled that off.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My second complaint came to me the other day when I was in the bath. It suddenly occurred to me that Humans, as awesome and mighty as we are, still only have the one planet. That is simply appalling to me. What is the point in living in the future if we cannot yet explore the cosmos and live among the stars? I understand that with all of the problems and pitfalls of running one planet you would be wary about taking on another, but you could easily appoint a governor or viceroy to watch over the new world. Hell, you could even name it after yourself! I would think that it would be a relief to you to know that out there is another world of humans that will continue the species even if you really screw things up here. I know that would take the edge off for me. Plus, it would be fun if we find a world inhabited by an equal or lesser species, because it would give us a chance to have a little War. You know how much we love War, and we don&#039;t get to do it that much anymore now that we&#039;re starting to realize how stupid it is to kill each other. If we found a nice, hostile planet, we could send everybody who wants to do War over there. That would sure make Earth seem nice and peaceful, wouldn&#039;t it? Who was the last world leader who could claim that he sent all War to an entirely different planet? Nobody, that&#039;s who.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are the limitless bounds of the cosmos a bit daunting for you? Don&#039;t worry, there are great works you can do for us here on home soil, too. You&#039;re probably already looking into this one, but I was at the movies the other day and I saw that movie about the iron man. There were two of them in the movie, and I thought it would be great if I had one of those, too. Then I could just fly to work and I could pick up cars and stuff. I know the movie wasn&#039;t real, but that&#039;s where you come in. You should tell somebody to make an iron man, and make sure that they make one big enough to fit a taller gentleman, like myself. In fact &amp;ndash; this is another point entirely, actually &amp;ndash; there&#039;s a lot you could do for tall people. For example, people never trim trees quite tall enough and I always end up bumping my head into branches and I get scratches on my face. Also the seats on planes are too small. Anyway, yeah, we should have iron mans. We could use them in our wars with other planets. When those stupid alien things see an army of flying metal dudes coming at them, they&#039;d totally poop their pants, if they could poop . . . or had pants. Shouldn&#039;t every human being be entitled to life, liberty, and the ability to be an Iron Man?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another thing: have you ever tried to park anywhere lately? Here in Chicago, they have these boxes where you pay to park, and you get a little sticker that you put in your window. While it works great, in theory, people don&#039;t know where the different parking spaces are, because each box applies to the whole block instead of each space separately. Now people just park wherever they feel like, leaving huge gaps in between each other, so all the spots run out of space, even for Smart Cars. It&#039;s a lot like communism, really. You&#039;re President of Earth; can&#039;t you do something about this? It would be better if you could do something rather soon, too, because I don&#039;t know how much longer this friend of mine can keep driving around the block looking for a space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You know, cars are pretty silly, if you get right down to it. I mean, we should just have tubes that go everywhere like in that show Futurama (there was even a President of Earth in Futurama, so you should be all over that). It would be just like at the bank. I think we should probably keep the &quot;no coins&quot; rule, too, because I don&#039;t want to get hit in the butt with a quarter when I&#039;m trying to go somewhere. Anyway, my Mom is way more obsessed about Tube Technology, and I&#039;m sure you&#039;ve probably gotten tons of letters from her already about that. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oh yeah, that was another complaint. Can&#039;t you get the Internet for my Parents yet? They&#039;re still stuck with just dial up access, and you probably don&#039;t need me to tell you that dial up blows. Granted, they live in the middle of Nowhere, but Nowhere is still on Earth, isn&#039;t it? Last time I checked, you were President of There. Please tell somebody to get off their ass and run some wires out there or something. It&#039;s the future, for crying out loud. If we had iron mans, you could send out an iron man and he could just fly there with his rocket boots and a . . . bunch of . . . internets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, why does everybody in the world still use physical money? Can&#039;t we all just get some sort of credit card? Sure, it would be a shock to the system, and a few industries would be affected, but we (humans) are pretty smart, so we&#039;ll probably figure it out. I think that the removal of physical currency would probably most impact the vagrancy industry. It would be hard for bums on the street to ask for spare change if spare change only existed as fractions in someone&#039;s digital bank account. I can see how that could be a problem. If all those bums were unable to panhandle, there would be a lot of people out of out of work, and then they&#039;ll get kicked out of out of their homes. Still, they&#039;ll probably learn to adapt, I&#039;m sure. You could issue credit card readers to the various tech-savy tramps roaming the streets. The others could finally get what they really want anyway, and just ask for booze; either that or - you know - get a job. You could always issue iron man suits to all the bums in the world. That would at least be really interesting to watch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Okay, these concerns seem daunting. I understand that. I mean, there you are, suddenly the most powerful human being on the planet, with a billion things to worry about (many of them in Spanish), and some random dude starts throwing his stupid problems at you? I mean, you&#039;re still struggling with the fact that you don&#039;t exist; how could you be expected to solve the lousy parking situation in Chicago, Illinois? I think, though, that as you look out of your two hundredth floor window at the developing Dubai skyline - a menagerie of cranes, bizarre structures and exposed girders - that the Human Race needs to pick itself up. We, as a species, need to get our Shit together.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Imagine, if you will, that you had a son (or if you have a son, picture a second son). Let&#039;s call him Gerald. Gerald just went off to college. He&#039;s living on his own, now, for the first time. You are happy for Gerald, and you know that he will do just fine. Gerald is a good kid; he&#039;s smart, full of vim (whatever that is), and ready to take on the world. However, you begin to receive complaints from Gerald&#039;s counselor or RA or whatever that he&#039;s starting to slip. Gerald is self-destructive, violent toward other students, greedy, irresponsible, ignoring his homework, and just a general asshole to the other students. Gerald has been trashing his dorm room and nobody can find his roommate, Passenger Pigeon (yeah, I went there). All Gerald does anymore is sit around drinking and playing video games. What would you do about that?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You would tell Gerald to get his Shit together (or perhaps a variation on that theme). To any outside observer, Gerald is a menace to the world around him. He desperately needs to be contained. He desperately needs a parental figure to tell him to shape up, and to let him know what will happen if he doesn&#039;t (either the world explodes or Dean of Students Global Climate Change will come down and murder him). I&#039;m simply asking you, as Leader of All of Us, to be that parental figure, and tell All of Us to shape up. Stick your head out that two hundredth floor window and yell, &quot;listen up everybody, we&#039;re not going to be like Gerald anymore.&quot; Get on that special red phone connected directly to Humanity and say, &quot;it&#039;s time to stop being a bunch of assholes, all seven billion of you.&quot; Tell your Secretary of Manning-up to get off his nonexistent ass and get to work. Open your eyes, bring yourself into existence, grab this planet by its giant blue marbles, and make it a better place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don&#039;t just do it for me. Don&#039;t do it for the children. Do it because if you don&#039;t do it people are going to call you a &quot;lame duck&quot; or a &quot;socialist&quot; or a &quot;made-up.&quot; Do it because if you don&#039;t we&#039;re all going to kill ourselves (I don&#039;t mean we&#039;re all going to commit suicide, I mean we&#039;re going to destroy ourselves by being assholes) if you don&#039;t. Do it because I really want an iron man suit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In conclusion, I really just want an iron man suit. Thank you in advance for making that happen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sincerely,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0px&quot;&gt;Shauvon McGill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0px&quot;&gt;DenyConformity.com&lt;/p&gt;
