&lt;p&gt;Two friends were doing really well in a class at college.  They were doing so well, in fact, that they decided that the weekend before the final, they would go to a huge party at another school.  They ended up getting back to school really late Sunday night, so they slept through the test on Monday morning.  They explained to the proffessor that they had gotten a flat tire coming back from the other college.  The proffessor understood, and allowed the two students to take the test the next day.  They spent the rest of the day studying.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;The next day, the proffessor put them in sepparate rooms, and gave them both a test booklet.  The first page, worth five points, was extremely easy.  Both students relaxed, knowing that they would ace the test.  Then they looked at the next question of the test, which read:&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&quot;(95 points) Which tire?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

